WORK_MODE.description: 0: single mode, 1: double mode, 2: alternate mode

SAR_SEL.description: 0: SAR1, 1: SAR2, only work for single SAR mode

SAR1_PATT_P_CLEAR.description: clear the pointer of pattern table for DIG ADC1 CTRL

SAR2_PATT_P_CLEAR.description: clear the pointer of pattern table for DIG ADC2 CTRL

DATA_SAR_SEL.description: 1: sar_sel will be coded by the MSB of the 16-bit output data, in this case the resolution should not be larger than 11 bits.

DATA_TO_I2S.description: 1: I2S input data is from SAR ADC (for DMA), 0: I2S input data is from GPIO matrix

XPD_SAR1_FORCE.description: force option to xpd sar1 blocks

XPD_SAR2_FORCE.description: force option to xpd sar2 blocks

WAIT_ARB_CYCLE.description: wait arbit signal stable after sar_done

SAR1_INV.description: 1: data to DIG ADC1 CTRL is inverted, otherwise not

SAR2_INV.description: 1: data to DIG ADC2 CTRL is inverted, otherwise not

SAR1_PATT_TAB1.description: item 0 ~ 3 for pattern table 1 (each item one byte)

SAR1_PATT_TAB2.description: Item 4 ~ 7 for pattern table 1 (each item one byte)

SAR1_PATT_TAB3.description: Item 8 ~ 11 for pattern table 1 (each item one byte)

SAR1_PATT_TAB4.description: Item 12 ~ 15 for pattern table 1 (each item one byte)

SAR2_PATT_TAB1.description: item 0 ~ 3 for pattern table 2 (each item one byte)

SAR2_PATT_TAB2.description: Item 4 ~ 7 for pattern table 2 (each item one byte)

SAR2_PATT_TAB3.description: Item 8 ~ 11 for pattern table 2 (each item one byte)

SAR2_PATT_TAB4.description: Item 12 ~ 15 for pattern table 2 (each item one byte)

ARB_APB_FORCE.description: adc2 arbiter force to enableapb controller

ARB_RTC_FORCE.description: adc2 arbiter force to enable rtc controller

ARB_WIFI_FORCE.description: adc2 arbiter force to enable wifi controller

APB_ADC_EOF_NUM.description: the dma_in_suc_eof gen when sample cnt = spi_eof_num

CLK_EN.description: need_des

IV_MEM[%s].description: The memory that stores initialization vector

H_MEM[%s].description: The memory that stores GCM hash subkey

AAD_BLOCK_NUM.description: Additional Authential Data block number register

KEY_0.description: This bits stores key_0 that is a part of key material.

KEY_1.description: This bits stores key_1 that is a part of key material.

KEY_2.description: This bits stores key_2 that is a part of key material.

KEY_3.description: This bits stores key_3 that is a part of key material.

KEY_4.description: This bits stores key_4 that is a part of key material.

KEY_5.description: This bits stores key_5 that is a part of key material.

KEY_6.description: This bits stores key_6 that is a part of key material.

KEY_7.description: This bits stores key_7 that is a part of key material.

TEXT_IN_0.description: This bits stores text_in_0 that is a part of source text material.

TEXT_IN_1.description: This bits stores text_in_1 that is a part of source text material.

TEXT_IN_2.description: This bits stores text_in_2 that is a part of source text material.

TEXT_IN_3.description: This bits stores text_in_3 that is a part of source text material.

TEXT_OUT_0.description: This bits stores text_out_0 that is a part of result text material.

TEXT_OUT_1.description: This bits stores text_out_1 that is a part of result text material.

TEXT_OUT_2.description: This bits stores text_out_2 that is a part of result text material.

TEXT_OUT_3.description: This bits stores text_out_3 that is a part of result text material.

MODE.description: This bits decides which one operation mode will be used. 3'd0: AES-EN-128, 3'd1: AES-EN-192, 3'd2: AES-EN-256, 3'd4: AES-DE-128, 3'd5: AES-DE-192, 3'd6: AES-DE-256.

ENDIAN.description: endian. [1:0] key endian, [3:2] text_in endian or in_stream endian,  [5:4] text_out endian or out_stream endian

TRIGGER.description: Set this bit to start AES calculation.

STATE.description: Those bits shows AES status. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

DMA_ENABLE.description: 1'b0: typical AES working mode, 1'b1: DMA-AES working mode.

BLOCK_MODE.description: Those bits decides which block mode will be used. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: GCM, 0x7: reserved.

BLOCK_NUM.description: Those bits stores the number of Plaintext/ciphertext block.

INC_SEL.description: This bit decides the standard incrementing function. 0: INC32. 1: INC128.

AAD_BLOCK_NUM.description: Those bits stores the number of AAD block.

REMAINDER_BIT_NUM.description: Those bits stores the number of remainder bit.

CONTINUE.description: Set this bit to continue GCM operation.

INT_CLEAR.description: Set this bit to clear the AES interrupt.

INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable interrupt that occurs when DMA-AES calculation is done.

DATE.description: This bits stores the version information of AES.

DMA_EXIT.description: Set this register to leave calculation done stage. Recommend to use it after software finishes reading DMA's output buffer.

IN_DONE_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0.

IN_SUC_EOF_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0. For UHCI0 the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

IN_ERR_EOF_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data error is detected only in the case that the peripheral is UHCI0 for Rx channel 0. For other peripherals this raw interrupt is reserved.

IN_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting inlink descriptor error including owner error and the second and third word error of inlink descriptor for Rx channel 0.

IN_DSCR_EMPTY_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Rx buffer pointed by inlink is full and receiving data is not completed but there is no more inlink for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_OVF_CH_INT_RAW.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is overflow.

INFIFO_UDF_CH_INT_RAW.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

INFIFO_UDF_CH_INT_ST.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the INFIFO_UDF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_DONE_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been transmitted to peripherals for Tx channel 0.

OUT_EOF_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been read from memory for Tx channel 0.

OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting outlink descriptor error including owner error and the second and third word error of outlink descriptor for Tx channel 0.

OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data corresponding a outlink (includes one link descriptor or few link descriptors) is transmitted out for Tx channel 0.

AHBM_RST_INTER.description: Set this bit then clear this bit to reset the internal ahb FSM.

ARB_PRI_DIS.description: Set this bit to disable priority arbitration function.

CLK_EN.description: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

IN_RST_CH.description: This bit is used to reset AHB_DMA channel 0 Rx FSM and Rx FIFO pointer.

INDSCR_BURST_EN_CH.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

IN_DATA_BURST_EN_CH.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 receiving data when accessing internal SRAM.

MEM_TRANS_EN_CH.description: Set this bit 1 to enable automatic transmitting data from memory to memory via AHB_DMA.

IN_ETM_EN_CH.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable etm control mode, dma Rx channel 0 is triggered by etm task.

IN_CHECK_OWNER_CH.description: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

INFIFO_FULL_CH.description: L1 Rx FIFO full signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_EMPTY_CH.description: L1 Rx FIFO empty signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_CNT_CH.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L1 Rx FIFO for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_RDATA_CH.description: This register stores the data popping from AHB_DMA FIFO.

INFIFO_POP_CH.description: Set this bit to pop data from AHB_DMA FIFO.

INLINK_AUTO_RET_CH.description: Set this bit to return to current inlink descriptor's address when there are some errors in current receiving data.

INLINK_STOP_CH.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the inlink descriptors.

INLINK_START_CH.description: Set this bit to start dealing with the inlink descriptors.

INLINK_RESTART_CH.description: Set this bit to mount a new inlink descriptor.

INLINK_PARK_CH.description: 1: the inlink descriptor's FSM is in idle state.  0: the inlink descriptor's FSM is working.

INLINK_DSCR_ADDR_CH.description: This register stores the current inlink descriptor's address.

IN_SUC_EOF_DES_ADDR_CH.description: This register stores the address of the inlink descriptor when the EOF bit in this descriptor is 1.

IN_ERR_EOF_DES_ADDR_CH.description: This register stores the address of the inlink descriptor when there are some errors in current receiving data. Only used when peripheral is UHCI0.

INLINK_DSCR_CH.description: The address of the current inlink descriptor x.

INLINK_DSCR_BF0_CH.description: The address of the last inlink descriptor x-1.

INLINK_DSCR_BF1_CH.description: The address of the second-to-last inlink descriptor x-2.

RX_PRI_CH.description: The priority of Rx channel 0. The larger of the value the higher of the priority.

PERI_IN_SEL_CH.description: This register is used to select peripheral for Rx channel 0. I3C. 1: Dummy. 2: UHCI0. 3: I2S0. 4: I2S1. 5: I2S2. 6: Dummy. 7: Dummy. 8: ADC_DAC. 9: Dummy. 10: RMT,11~15: Dummy

OUT_RST_CH0.description: This bit is used to reset AHB_DMA channel 0 Tx FSM and Tx FIFO pointer.

OUT_AUTO_WRBACK_CH0.description: Set this bit to enable automatic outlink-writeback when all the data in tx buffer has been transmitted.

OUT_EOF_MODE_CH0.description: EOF flag generation mode when transmitting data. 1: EOF flag for Tx channel 0 is generated when data need to transmit has been popped from FIFO in AHB_DMA

OUTDSCR_BURST_EN_CH0.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 0 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

OUT_DATA_BURST_EN_CH0.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 0 transmitting data when accessing internal SRAM.

OUT_ETM_EN_CH0.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable etm control mode, dma Tx channel 0 is triggered by etm task.

OUT_CHECK_OWNER_CH.description: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

OUTFIFO_FULL_CH.description: L1 Tx FIFO full signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_EMPTY_CH.description: L1 Tx FIFO empty signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_CNT_CH.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L1 Tx FIFO for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_WDATA_CH.description: This register stores the data that need to be pushed into AHB_DMA FIFO.

OUTFIFO_PUSH_CH.description: Set this bit to push data into AHB_DMA FIFO.

OUTLINK_STOP_CH.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the outlink descriptors.

OUTLINK_START_CH.description: Set this bit to start dealing with the outlink descriptors.

OUTLINK_RESTART_CH.description: Set this bit to restart a new outlink from the last address.

OUTLINK_PARK_CH.description: 1: the outlink descriptor's FSM is in idle state.  0: the outlink descriptor's FSM is working.

OUTLINK_DSCR_ADDR_CH.description: This register stores the current outlink descriptor's address.

OUT_EOF_DES_ADDR_CH.description: This register stores the address of the outlink descriptor when the EOF bit in this descriptor is 1.

OUT_EOF_BFR_DES_ADDR_CH.description: This register stores the address of the outlink descriptor before the last outlink descriptor.

OUTLINK_DSCR_CH.description: The address of the current outlink descriptor y.

OUTLINK_DSCR_BF0_CH.description: The address of the last outlink descriptor y-1.

OUTLINK_DSCR_BF1_CH.description: The address of the second-to-last inlink descriptor x-2.

TX_PRI_CH.description: The priority of Tx channel 0. The larger of the value the higher of the priority.

PERI_OUT_SEL_CH.description: This register is used to select peripheral for Tx channel 0. I3C. 1: Dummy. 2: UHCI0. 3: I2S0. 4: I2S1. 5: I2S2. 6: Dummy. 7: Dummy. 8: ADC_DAC. 9: Dummy. 10: RMT,11~15: Dummy

OUT_RST_CH.description: This bit is used to reset AHB_DMA channel 1 Tx FSM and Tx FIFO pointer.

OUT_AUTO_WRBACK_CH.description: Set this bit to enable automatic outlink-writeback when all the data in tx buffer has been transmitted.

OUT_EOF_MODE_CH.description: EOF flag generation mode when transmitting data. 1: EOF flag for Tx channel 1 is generated when data need to transmit has been popped from FIFO in AHB_DMA

OUTDSCR_BURST_EN_CH.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 1 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

OUT_DATA_BURST_EN_CH.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 1 transmitting data when accessing internal SRAM.

OUT_ETM_EN_CH.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable etm control mode, dma Tx channel 1 is triggered by etm task.

OUT_CRC_CLEAR_CH.description: This register is used to clear ch0 of tx crc result

TX_INST_IDX.description: write this bits to specify the one of 8 instruction

TX_INST_POS.description: write this bits to specify the bit position of 257 bit instruction which in units of 32 bits

TX_INST.description: write this bits to update instruction which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_TX_INST_CFG0_REG, Read this bits to get instruction which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_TX_INST_CFG0_REG

RX_INST_IDX.description: write this bits to specify the one of 8 instruction

RX_INST_POS.description: write this bits to specify the bit position of 257 bit instruction which in units of 32 bits

RX_INST.description: write this bits to update instruction which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_RX_INST_CFG0_REG, Read this bits to get instruction which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_RX_INST_CFG0_REG

TX_LUT_IDX.description: write this bits to specify the bytes position of LUT RAM based on reg_bitscrambler_tx_lut_mode

TX_LUT_MODE.description: write this bits to specify the bytes mode of LUT RAM, 0: 1 byte,1: 2bytes, 2: 4 bytes

TX_LUT.description: write this bits to update LUT which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_TX_LUT_CFG0_REG, Read this bits to get LUT which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_TX_LUT_CFG0_REG

RX_LUT_IDX.description: write this bits to specify the bytes position of LUT RAM based on reg_bitscrambler_rx_lut_mode

RX_LUT_MODE.description: write this bits to specify the bytes mode of LUT RAM, 0: 1 byte,1: 2bytes, 2: 4 bytes

RX_LUT.description: write this bits to update LUT which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_RX_LUT_CFG0_REG, Read this bits to get LUT which specified by BITSCRAMBLER_RX_LUT_CFG0_REG

TX_TAILING_BITS.description: write this bits to specify the extra data bit length after getting EOF

RX_TAILING_BITS.description: write this bits to specify the extra data bit length after getting EOF

TX_ENA.description: write this bit to enable the bitscrambler tx

TX_PAUSE.description: write this bit to pause the bitscrambler tx core

TX_HALT.description: write this bit to halt the bitscrambler tx core

TX_EOF_MODE.description: write this bit to ser the bitscrambler tx core EOF signal generating mode which is combined with reg_bitscrambler_tx_tailing_bits, 0: counter by read dma fifo, 0 counter by write peripheral buffer

TX_COND_MODE.description: write this bit to specify the LOOP instruction condition mode of bitscrambler tx core, 0: use the little than operator to get the condition, 1: use not equal operator to get the condition

TX_FETCH_MODE.description: write this bit to set the bitscrambler tx core fetch instruction mode, 0: prefetch by reset, 1: fetch by instrutions

TX_HALT_MODE.description: write this bit to set the bitscrambler tx core halt mode when tx_halt is set, 0: wait write data back done, , 1: ignore write data back

TX_RD_DUMMY.description: write this bit to set the bitscrambler tx core read data mode when EOF received.0: wait read data, 1: ignore read data

TX_FIFO_RST.description: write this bit to reset the bitscrambler tx fifo

RX_ENA.description: write this bit to enable the bitscrambler rx

RX_PAUSE.description: write this bit to pause the bitscrambler rx core

RX_HALT.description: write this bit to halt the bitscrambler rx core

RX_EOF_MODE.description: write this bit to ser the bitscrambler rx core EOF signal generating mode which is combined with reg_bitscrambler_rx_tailing_bits, 0: counter by read peripheral buffer, 0 counter by write dma fifo

RX_COND_MODE.description: write this bit to specify the LOOP instruction condition mode of bitscrambler rx core, 0: use the little than operator to get the condition, 1: use not equal operator to get the condition

RX_FETCH_MODE.description: write this bit to set the bitscrambler rx core fetch instruction mode, 0: prefetch by reset, 1: fetch by instrutions

RX_HALT_MODE.description: write this bit to set the bitscrambler rx core halt mode when rx_halt is set, 0: wait write data back done, , 1: ignore write data back

RX_RD_DUMMY.description: write this bit to set the bitscrambler rx core read data mode when EOF received.0: wait read data, 1: ignore read data

RX_FIFO_RST.description: write this bit to reset the bitscrambler rx fifo

TX_IN_IDLE.description: represents the bitscrambler tx core in halt mode

TX_IN_RUN.description: represents the bitscrambler tx core in run mode

TX_IN_WAIT.description: represents the bitscrambler tx core in wait mode to wait write back done

TX_IN_PAUSE.description: represents the bitscrambler tx core in pause mode

TX_FIFO_EMPTY.description: represents the bitscrambler tx fifo in empty state

TX_EOF_GET_CNT.description: represents the bytes numbers of bitscrambler tx core when get EOF

TX_EOF_OVERLOAD.description: represents the some EOFs will be lost for bitscrambler tx core

TX_EOF_TRACE_CLR.description: write this bit to clear reg_bitscrambler_tx_eof_overload and reg_bitscrambler_tx_eof_get_cnt registers

RX_IN_IDLE.description: represents the bitscrambler rx core in halt mode

RX_IN_RUN.description: represents the bitscrambler rx core in run mode

RX_IN_WAIT.description: represents the bitscrambler rx core in wait mode to wait write back done

RX_IN_PAUSE.description: represents the bitscrambler rx core in pause mode

RX_FIFO_FULL.description: represents the bitscrambler rx fifo in full state

RX_EOF_GET_CNT.description: represents the bytes numbers of bitscrambler rx core when get EOF

RX_EOF_OVERLOAD.description: represents the some EOFs will be lost for bitscrambler rx core

RX_EOF_TRACE_CLR.description: write this bit to clear reg_bitscrambler_rx_eof_overload and reg_bitscrambler_rx_eof_get_cnt registers

LOOP_MODE.description: write this bit to set the bitscrambler tx loop back to DMA rx

LOCK_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable lock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after lock operation done. Note that (1) this bit and unlock_ena bit are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time. (2) lock operation can be applied on LL1-ICache, L1-DCache and L2-Cache.

UNLOCK_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable unlock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after unlock operation done. Note that (1) this bit and lock_ena bit are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time. (2) unlock operation can be applied on L1-ICache, L1-DCache and L2-Cache.

LOCK_DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether unlock/lock operation is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

LOCK_RGID.description: The bit is used to set  the gid of cache lock/unlock.

LOCK_MAP.description: Those bits are used to indicate which caches in the two-level cache structure will apply this lock/unlock operation. [0]: L1-ICache0, [1]: L1-ICache1, [2]: L1-ICache2, [3]: L1-ICache3, [4]: L1-DCache, [5]: L2-Cache.

LOCK_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the lock/unlock operation, which should be used together with CACHE_LOCK_SIZE_REG

LOCK_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the lock/unlock operation, which should be used together with CACHE_LOCK_ADDR_REG

INVALIDATE_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after invalidate operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (clean_ena, writeback_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

CLEAN_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable clean operation. It will be cleared by hardware after clean operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, writeback_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

WRITEBACK_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable writeback operation. It will be cleared by hardware after writeback operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, clean_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

WRITEBACK_INVALIDATE_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable writeback-invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after writeback-invalidate operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, clean_ena, writeback_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

SYNC_DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether sync operation (invalidate, clean, writeback, writeback_invalidate) is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

SYNC_RGID.description: The bit is used to set  the gid of cache sync operation (invalidate, clean, writeback, writeback_invalidate)

SYNC_MAP.description: Those bits are used to indicate which caches in the two-level cache structure will apply the sync operation. [0]: L1-ICache0, [1]: L1-ICache1, [2]: L1-ICache2, [3]: L1-ICache3, [4]: L1-DCache, [5]: L2-Cache.

SYNC_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the sync operation, which should be used together with CACHE_SYNC_SIZE_REG

SYNC_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the sync operation, which should be used together with CACHE_SYNC_ADDR_REG

L1_ICACHE0_PRELOAD_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable preload operation on L1-ICache0. It will be cleared by hardware automatically after preload operation is done.

L1_ICACHE0_PRELOAD_DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether preload operation is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

L1_ICACHE0_PRELOAD_ORDER.description: The bit is used to configure the direction of preload operation. 0: ascending, 1: descending.

L1_ICACHE0_PRELOAD_RGID.description: The bit is used to set  the gid of l1 icache0 preload.

L1_ICACHE2_FAIL_ID.description: The register records the ID of fail-access when cache2 accesses L1-ICache.

L1_ICACHE2_FAIL_ATTR.description: The register records the attribution of fail-access when cache2 accesses L1-ICache.

L1_ICACHE2_FAIL_ADDR.description: The register records the address of fail-access when cache2 accesses L1-ICache.

L1_ICACHE3_FAIL_ID.description: The register records the ID of fail-access when cache3 accesses L1-ICache.

L1_ICACHE3_FAIL_ATTR.description: The register records the attribution of fail-access when cache3 accesses L1-ICache.

L1_ICACHE3_FAIL_ADDR.description: The register records the address of fail-access when cache3 accesses L1-ICache.

L1_DCACHE_FAIL_ID.description: The register records the ID of fail-access when cache accesses L1-DCache.

L1_DCACHE_FAIL_ATTR.description: The register records the attribution of fail-access when cache accesses L1-DCache.

L1_DCACHE_FAIL_ADDR.description: The register records the address of fail-access when cache accesses L1-DCache.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_DONE_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L1-ICache0 preload-operation. If preload operation is done, interrupt occurs.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_DONE_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L1-ICache1 preload-operation. If preload operation is done, interrupt occurs.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L1-DCache preload-operation. If preload operation is done, interrupt occurs.

SYNC_DONE_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of Cache sync-operation done.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L1-ICache0 preload-operation error.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L1-ICache1 preload-operation error.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L1-DCache preload-operation error.

SYNC_ERR_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of Cache sync-operation error.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_DONE_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache0 preload-operation is done.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_DONE_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache1 preload-operation is done.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt that occurs only when L1-DCache preload-operation is done.

SYNC_DONE_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt that occurs only when Cache sync-operation is done.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt of L1-ICache0 preload-operation error.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt of L1-ICache1 preload-operation error.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt of L1-DCache preload-operation error.

SYNC_ERR_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt of Cache sync-operation error.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache0 preload-operation is done.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache1 preload-operation is done.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-DCache preload-operation is done.

SYNC_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when Cache sync-operation is done.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache0 preload-operation error occurs.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache1 preload-operation error occurs.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-DCache preload-operation error occurs.

SYNC_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when Cache sync-operation error occurs.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_DONE_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache0 preload-operation is done.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_DONE_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache1 preload-operation is done.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-DCache preload-operation is done.

SYNC_DONE_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when Cache sync-operation is done.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-ICache0 preload-operation error.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-ICache1 preload-operation error.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-DCache preload-operation error.

SYNC_ERR_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of Cache sync-operation error.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_CODE.description: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-ICache0.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_CODE.description: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-ICache1.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_ERR_CODE.description: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-DCache.

SYNC_ERR_CODE.description: The values 0-2 are available which means sync map, command conflict and size are error in Cache System.

L1_ICACHE0_SYNC_RST.description: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-ICache0. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

L1_ICACHE1_SYNC_RST.description: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-ICache1. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

L1_DCACHE_SYNC_RST.description: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-DCache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

L1_ICACHE0_PLD_RST.description: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-ICache0. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

L1_ICACHE1_PLD_RST.description: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-ICache1. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

L1_DCACHE_PLD_RST.description: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-DCache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

L1_ICACHE0_ALD_BUF_CLR.description: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-ICache0. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-ICache0. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-ICache0.

L1_ICACHE1_ALD_BUF_CLR.description: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-ICache1. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-ICache1. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-ICache1.

L1_DCACHE_ALD_BUF_CLR.description: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-DCache. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-DCache. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-DCache.

L1_ICACHE0_UNALLOC_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 icache0 where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

L1_ICACHE1_UNALLOC_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 icache1 where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

L1_DCACHE_UNALLOC_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 dcache where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

L1_ICACHE0_TAG_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L1-ICache0 tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L1_ICACHE1_TAG_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L1-ICache1 tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L1_DCACHE_TAG_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L1-DCache tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L1_ICACHE0_MEM_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L1-ICache0 data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L1_ICACHE1_MEM_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L1-ICache1 data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L1_DCACHE_MEM_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L1-DCache data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L1_CACHE_WAY_OBJECT.description: Set this bits to select which way of the tag-object will be accessed. 0: way0, 1: way1, 2: way2, 3: way3, ?, 7: way7.

L1_CACHE_VADDR.description: Those bits stores the virtual address which will decide where inside the specified tag memory object will be accessed.

L1_CACHE_DEBUG_BUS.description: This is a constant place where we can write data to or read data from the tag/data memory on the specified cache.

L2_CACHE_SHUT_DMA.description: The bit is used to disable DMA access L2-Cache, 0: enable, 1: disable

BYPASS_L2_CACHE_EN.description: The bit is used to enable bypass L2-Cache. 0: disable bypass, 1: enable bypass.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_256.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 256 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_512.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 512 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_1K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 1k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_2K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 2k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_4K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 4k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_8K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 8k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_16K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 16k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_32K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 32k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_64K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 64k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_128K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 128k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_256K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 256k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_512K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 512k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_1024K.description: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 1024k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_8.description: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 8 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_16.description: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 16 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_32.description: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 32 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_64.description: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 64 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_128.description: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 128 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_256.description: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 256 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

L2_CACHE_WRAP.description: Set this bit as 1 to enable L2-Cache wrap around mode.

L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_ON.description: The bit is used to close clock gating of  L2-Cache tag memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PD.description: The bit is used to power L2-Cache tag memory down. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power down

L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PU.description: The bit is used to power L2-Cache tag memory up. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power up

L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_ON.description: The bit is used to close clock gating of  L2-Cache data memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_PD.description: The bit is used to power L2-Cache data memory down. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power down

L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_PU.description: The bit is used to power L2-Cache data memory up. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power up

L2_CACHE_FREEZE_EN.description: The bit is used to enable freeze operation on L2-Cache. It can be cleared by software.

L2_CACHE_FREEZE_MODE.description: The bit is used to configure mode of freeze operation L2-Cache. 0: a miss-access will not stuck. 1: a miss-access will stuck.

L2_CACHE_FREEZE_DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether freeze operation on L2-Cache is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_RD_EN.description: The bit is used to enable config-bus read L2-Cache data memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_WR_EN.description: The bit is used to enable config-bus write L2-Cache data memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_RD_EN.description: The bit is used to enable config-bus read L2-Cache tag memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_WR_EN.description: The bit is used to enable config-bus write L2-Cache tag memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_EN.description: The bit is used to enable the first section of prelock function on L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_EN.description: The bit is used to enable the second section of prelock function on L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_RGID.description: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache prelock.

L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE_REG

L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the second section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE_REG

L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR_REG

L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the second section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR_REG

L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable preload operation on L2-Cache. It will be cleared by hardware automatically after preload operation is done.

L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether preload operation is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ORDER.description: The bit is used to configure the direction of preload operation. 0: ascending, 1: descending.

L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_RGID.description: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache preload.

L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of preload on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE_REG

L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR_REG

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable and disable autoload operation on L2-Cache.  1: enable, 0: disable.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether autoload operation on L2-Cache is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_ORDER.description: The bit is used to configure the direction of autoload operation on L2-Cache. 0: ascending. 1: descending.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_TRIGGER_MODE.description: The field is used to configure trigger mode of autoload operation on L2-Cache. 0/3: miss-trigger, 1: hit-trigger, 2: miss-hit-trigger.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the first section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the second section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the third section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the fourth section for autoload operation on L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_RGID.description: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache autoload.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the first section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ENA.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ENA.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the second section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ENA.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the second section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ENA.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the third section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ENA.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the third section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT2_ENA.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ADDR.description: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the fourth section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_SIZE and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ENA.

L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_SIZE.description: Those bits are used to configure the size of the fourth section for autoload operation on L2-Cache. Note that it should be used together with L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ADDR and L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT3_ENA.

L2_IBUS0_OVF_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS1_OVF_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS0_OVF_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS1_OVF_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS0_OVF_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear counters overflow interrupt and counters in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS1_OVF_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear counters overflow interrupt and counters in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS0_OVF_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear counters overflow interrupt and counters in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS1_OVF_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear counters overflow interrupt and counters in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS0_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-ICache0.

L2_IBUS1_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-ICache1.

L2_IBUS2_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus2 accesses L2-ICache2.

L2_IBUS3_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus3 accesses L2-ICache3.

L2_DBUS0_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-DCache.

L2_DBUS1_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-DCache.

L2_DBUS2_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus2 accesses L2-DCache.

L2_DBUS3_OVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus3 accesses L2-DCache.

L2_IBUS0_OVF_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the interrupt status of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS1_OVF_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the interrupt status of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS0_OVF_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the interrupt status of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus0 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS1_OVF_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the interrupt status of one of counters overflow that occurs in L2-Cache due to bus1 accesses L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_ACS_FAIL_CHECK_MODE.description: The bit is used to configure l2 cache access fail check mode. 0: the access fail is not propagated to the request, 1: the access fail is propagated to the request

L2_CACHE_FAIL_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of access fail that occurs in L2-Cache due to l1 cache accesses L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_FAIL_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt of access fail that occurs in L2-Cache due to l1 cache accesses L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_FAIL_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt of access fail that occurs in L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_FAIL_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the interrupt status of access fail that occurs in L2-Cache due to l1 cache accesses L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS0_CNT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable ibus0 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS1_CNT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable ibus1 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS0_CNT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable dbus0 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS1_CNT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable dbus1 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS0_CNT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear ibus0 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS1_CNT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear ibus1 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS0_CNT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear dbus0 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_DBUS1_CNT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear dbus1 counter in L2-Cache.

L2_IBUS0_HIT_CNT.description: The register records the number of hits when L1-ICache0 accesses L2-Cache due to bus0 accessing L1-ICache0.

L2_IBUS0_MISS_CNT.description: The register records the number of missing when L1-ICache0 accesses L2-Cache due to bus0 accessing L1-ICache0.

L2_IBUS0_CONFLICT_CNT.description: The register records the number of access-conflicts when L1-ICache0 accesses L2-Cache due to bus0 accessing L1-ICache0.

L2_IBUS0_NXTLVL_RD_CNT.description: The register records the number of times that L2-Cache accesses external memory due to L1-ICache0 accessing L2-Cache due to bus0 accessing L1-ICache0.

L2_IBUS1_HIT_CNT.description: The register records the number of hits when L1-ICache1 accesses L2-Cache due to bus1 accessing L1-ICache1.

L2_IBUS1_MISS_CNT.description: The register records the number of missing when L1-ICache1 accesses L2-Cache due to bus1 accessing L1-ICache1.

L2_IBUS1_CONFLICT_CNT.description: The register records the number of access-conflicts when L1-ICache1 accesses L2-Cache due to bus1 accessing L1-ICache1.

L2_IBUS1_NXTLVL_RD_CNT.description: The register records the number of times that L2-Cache accesses external memory due to L1-ICache1 accessing L2-Cache due to bus1 accessing L1-ICache1.

L2_IBUS2_HIT_CNT.description: The register records the number of hits when L1-ICache2 accesses L2-Cache due to bus2 accessing L1-ICache2.

L2_IBUS2_MISS_CNT.description: The register records the number of missing when L1-ICache2 accesses L2-Cache due to bus2 accessing L1-ICache2.

L2_IBUS2_CONFLICT_CNT.description: The register records the number of access-conflicts when L1-ICache2 accesses L2-Cache due to bus2 accessing L1-ICache2.

L2_DBUS1_NXTLVL_RD_CNT.description: The register records the number of times that L2-Cache accesses external memory due to L1-DCache accessing L2-Cache due to bus1 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_DBUS2_MISS_CNT.description: The register records the number of missing when L1-DCache accesses L2-Cache due to bus2 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_DBUS2_CONFLICT_CNT.description: The register records the number of access-conflicts when L1-DCache accesses L2-Cache due to bus2 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_DBUS2_NXTLVL_RD_CNT.description: The register records the number of times that L2-Cache accesses external memory due to L1-DCache accessing L2-Cache due to bus2 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_DBUS2_NXTLVL_WR_CNT.description: The register records the number of write back when L1-DCache accesses L2-Cache due to bus2 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_DBUS3_MISS_CNT.description: The register records the number of missing when L1-DCache accesses L2-Cache due to bus3 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_DBUS3_NXTLVL_RD_CNT.description: The register records the number of times that L2-Cache accesses external memory due to L1-DCache accessing L2-Cache due to bus3 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_DBUS3_NXTLVL_WR_CNT.description: The register records the number of write back when L1-DCache accesses L2-Cache due to bus3 accessing L1-DCache.

L2_CACHE_FAIL_ID.description: The register records the ID of fail-access when L1-Cache accesses L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_FAIL_ATTR.description: The register records the attribution of fail-access when L1-Cache accesses L2-Cache due to cache accessing L1-Cache.

L2_CACHE_FAIL_ADDR.description: The register records the address of fail-access when L1-Cache accesses L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L2-Cache preload-operation done.

L2_CACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable interrupt of L2-Cache preload-operation error.

L2_CACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt that occurs only when L2-Cache preload-operation is done.

L2_CACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear interrupt of L2-Cache preload-operation error.

L2_CACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L2-Cache preload-operation is done.

L2_CACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw bit of the interrupt that occurs only when L2-Cache preload-operation error occurs.

L2_CACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L2-Cache preload-operation is done.

L2_CACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_ST.description: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L2-Cache preload-operation error.

L2_CACHE_PLD_ERR_CODE.description: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_SYNC_RST.description: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L2-Cache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

L2_CACHE_PLD_RST.description: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L2-Cache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

L2_CACHE_ALD_BUF_CLR.description: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L2-Cache. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L2-Cache. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L2-Cache.

L2_CACHE_UNALLOC_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l2 icache where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_CC.description: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with cacheable attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of cacheable and non-cacheable.

L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_WB.description: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with write-back attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of write-back and write-through.

L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_WMA.description: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with write-miss-allocate attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of write-miss-allocate and write-miss-no-allocate.

L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_RMA.description: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with read-miss-allocate attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of read-miss-allocate and read-miss-no-allocate.

L2_CACHE_TAG_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L2-Cache tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L2_CACHE_MEM_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set L2-Cache data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

L2_CACHE_WAY_OBJECT.description: Set this bits to select which way of the tag-object will be accessed. 0: way0, 1: way1, 2: way2, 3: way3, ?, 7: way7.

L2_CACHE_VADDR.description: Those bits stores the virtual address which will decide where inside the specified tag memory object will be accessed.

L2_CACHE_DEBUG_BUS.description: This is a constant place where we can write data to or read data from the tag/data memory on the specified cache.

CLK_EN.description: The bit is used to enable clock gate when access all registers in this module.

REDCY_SIG0.description: Those bits are prepared for ECO.

REDCY_SIG1.description: Those bits are prepared for ECO.

REDCY_SIG2.description: Those bits are prepared for ECO.

REDCY_SIG3.description: Those bits are prepared for ECO.

REDCY_SIG4.description: Those bits are prepared for ECO.

DATE.description: version control register. Note that this default value stored is the latest date when the hardware logic was updated.

CLK_EN.description: csi bridge register mapping unit clock gating.

HOST_CTRL.description: csi host control by csi bridge.

CLK_EN.description: 0: enable clock gating. 1: disable clock gating, clock always on.

CSI_BRIG_EN.description: 0: disable csi bridge. 1: enable csi bridge.

DMA_CFG_UPD_BY_BLK.description: 1: reg_dma_burst_len & reg_dma_burst_len will be updated by dma block finish. 0: updated by frame.

DMA_FORCE_RD_STATUS.description: 1: mask dma request when reading frame info. 0: disable mask.

DATA_TYPE_MIN.description: the min value of data type used for pixel filter.

DATA_TYPE_MAX.description: the max value of data type used for pixel filter.

HAS_HSYNC_E.description: 0: frame data doesn't contain hsync. 1: frame data contains hsync.

VADR_NUM_CHECK.description: 0: disable vadr check. 1: enable vadr check.

BYTE_ENDIAN_ORDER.description: endianness order in bytes. 2'h0 is normal mode and 2'h3 is useful to YUV420(Legacy) when isp is bapassed.

VADR_NUM_GT_INT_RAW.description: reg_vadr_num is greater than real interrupt raw.

VADR_NUM_LT_INT_RAW.description: reg_vadr_num is less than real interrupt raw.

DISCARD_INT_RAW.description: an incomplete frame of data was sent interrupt raw.

DMA_CFG_HAS_UPDATED_INT_RAW.description: dma configuration update complete interrupt raw.

VADR_NUM_GT_REAL_INT_CLR.description: reg_vadr_num is greater than real interrupt clr.

VADR_NUM_LT_REAL_INT_CLR.description: reg_vadr_num is less than real interrupt clr.

DISCARD_INT_CLR.description: an incomplete frame of data was sent interrupt clr.

DMA_CFG_HAS_UPDATED_INT_CLR.description: dma configuration update complete interrupt clr.

VADR_NUM_GT_INT_ST.description: reg_vadr_num is greater than real interrupt st.

VADR_NUM_LT_INT_ST.description: reg_vadr_num is less than real interrupt st.

DISCARD_INT_ST.description: an incomplete frame of data was sent interrupt st.

DMA_CFG_HAS_UPDATED_INT_ST.description: dma configuration update complete interrupt st.

VADR_NUM_GT_INT_ENA.description: reg_vadr_num is greater than real interrupt enable.

VADR_NUM_LT_INT_ENA.description: reg_vadr_num is less than real interrupt enable.

DISCARD_INT_ENA.description: an incomplete frame of data was sent interrupt enable.

DMA_CFG_HAS_UPDATED_INT_ENA.description: dma configuration update complete interrupt enable.

DMABLK_SIZE.description: the number of reg_dma_burst_len in a block

CSI_ENABLECLK.description: enable clock lane module of csi phy.

CSI_CFG_CLK_EN.description: enable cfg_clk of csi host module.

LOOPBK_TEST_EN.description: for phy test by loopback dsi phy to csi phy.

CSI_BRIDGE_MEM_CLK_FORCE_ON.description: csi bridge memory clock gating force on.

SET_START.description: set this bit to start DS operation.

SET_CONTINUE.description: set this bit to continue DS operation.

SET_FINISH.description: Set this bit to finish DS process.

MD_ERROR.description: MD checkout result. 1'b0: MD check pass, 1'b1: MD check fail

PADDING_BAD.description: padding checkout result. 1'b0: a good padding, 1'b1: a bad padding

MULT_INT_RAW.description: ECC interrupt raw register, valid in level.

CALC_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt status bit  for the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

CALC_DONE_INT_ST.description: The masked interrupt status bit  for the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

CALC_DONE_INT_ENA.description: The interrupt enable bit  for the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

CALC_DONE_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

START.description: Write 1 to start caculation of ECC Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after the caculatrion is done.

KEY_LENGTH.description: The key length mode bit of ECC Accelerator.  0: P-192.  1: P-256.

MOD_BASE.description: The mod base of mod operation, only valid in work_mode 8-11. 0: n(order of curve). 1: p(mod base of curve)

WORK_MODE.description: The work mode bits of ECC Accelerator. 0: Point Mult Mode. 1: Reserved. 2: Point verification mode. 3: Point Verif+mult mode. 4: Jacobian Point Mult Mode. 5: Point Add Mode. 6: Jacobian Point Verification Mode. 7: Point Verif + Jacobian Mult Mode. 8: mod addition. 9. mod substraction. 10: mod multiplication. 11: mod division.

VERIFICATION_RESULT.description: The verification result bit of ECC Accelerator, only valid when calculation is done.

CLK_EN.description: Write 1 to force on register clock gate.

MEM_CLOCK_GATE_FORCE_ON.description: ECC memory clock gate force on register

INT_RAW.description: ECDSA interrupt raw register, valid in level.

Z_MEM[%s].description: The memory that stores software written z.

QAX_MEM[%s].description: The memory that stores x coordinates of QA or software written k.

QAY_MEM[%s].description: The memory that stores y coordinates of QA.

WORK_MODE.description: The work mode bits of ECDSA Accelerator. 0: Signature Verify Mode. 1: Signature Generate Mode. 2: Export Public Key Mode. 3: invalid.

ECC_CURVE.description: The ecc curve select bit of ECDSA Accelerator.  0: P-192.  1: P-256.

SOFTWARE_SET_K.description: The source of k select bit. 0: k is automatically generated by hardware. 1: k is written by software.

SOFTWARE_SET_Z.description: The source of z select bit. 0: z is generated from SHA result. 1: z is written by software.

DETERMINISTIC_K.description: The source of hardware generated k. 0: k is generated by TRNG. 1: k is generated by deterministic derivation algorithm.

DETERMINISTIC_LOOP.description: The (loop number - 1) value in the deterministic derivation algorithm to derive k.

GATE_FORCE_ON.description: Write 1 to force on register clock gate.

CALC_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt status bit  for the ecdsa_calc_done_int interrupt

SHA_RELEASE_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt status bit  for the ecdsa_sha_release_int interrupt

SHA_RELEASE_INT_ST.description: The masked interrupt status bit  for the ecdsa_sha_release_int interrupt

SHA_RELEASE_INT_ENA.description: The interrupt enable bit  for the ecdsa_sha_release_int interrupt

CALC_DONE_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the ecdsa_calc_done_int interrupt

SHA_RELEASE_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the ecdsa_sha_release_int interrupt

START.description: Write 1 to start caculation of ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

LOAD_DONE.description: Write 1 to input load done signal of ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

GET_DONE.description: Write 1 to input get done signal of ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

BUSY.description: The status bits of ECDSA Accelerator. ECDSA is at 0: IDLE, 1: LOAD, 2: GET, 3: BUSY state.

OPERATION_RESULT.description: The operation result bit of ECDSA Accelerator, only valid when ECDSA calculation is done.

K_VALUE_WARNING.description: The k value warning bit of ECDSA Accelerator, valid when k value is bigger than the curve order, then actually taken k = k mod n.

SHA_MODE.description: The work mode bits of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. 1: SHA-224. 2: SHA-256. Others: invalid.

SHA_START.description: Write 1 to start the first caculation of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

SHA_CONTINUE.description: Write 1 to start the latter caculation of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

SHA_BUSY.description: The busy status bit of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. 1:SHA is in calculation. 0: SHA is idle.

PGM_CHECK_VALUE1.description: Register 1 that stores the RS code to be programmed.

PGM_CHECK_VALUE2.description: Register 2 that stores the RS code to be programmed.

RD_REPEAT_ERR0.description: Programming error record register 0 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR1.description: Programming error record register 1 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR2.description: Programming error record register 2 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR3.description: Programming error record register 3 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR4.description: Programming error record register 4 of BLOCK0.

RD_RS_ERR0.description: Programming error record register 0 of BLOCK1-10.

RD_RS_ERR1.description: Programming error record register 1 of BLOCK1-10.

WR_TIM_CONF1.description: Configurarion register 1 of eFuse programming timing parameters.

WR_TIM_CONF2.description: Configurarion register 2 of eFuse programming timing parameters.

WR_TIM_CONF0_RS_BYPASS.description: Configurarion register0 of eFuse programming time parameters and rs bypass operation.

PGM_DATA_0.description: Configures the 0th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_1.description: Configures the 1st 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_2.description: Configures the 2nd 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_3.description: Configures the 3rd 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_4.description: Configures the 4th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_5.description: Configures the 5th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_6.description: Configures the 6th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_7.description: Configures the 7th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_RS_DATA_0.description: Configures the 0th 32-bit RS code to be programmed.

PGM_RS_DATA_1.description: Configures the 1st 32-bit RS code to be programmed.

PGM_RS_DATA_2.description: Configures the 2nd 32-bit RS code to be programmed.

WR_DIS.description: Represents whether programming of individual eFuse memory bit is disabled or enabled. 1: Disabled. 0 Enabled.

RD_DIS.description: Represents whether reading of individual eFuse block(block4~block10) is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

USB_DEVICE_EXCHG_PINS.description: Enable usb device exchange pins of D+ and D-.

USB_OTG11_EXCHG_PINS.description: Enable usb otg11 exchange pins of D+ and D-.

DIS_USB_JTAG.description: Represents whether the function of usb switch to jtag is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

POWERGLITCH_EN.description: Represents whether power glitch function is enabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

DIS_USB_SERIAL_JTAG.description: Represents whether USB-Serial-JTAG is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

DIS_FORCE_DOWNLOAD.description: Represents whether the function that forces chip into download mode is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

SPI_DOWNLOAD_MSPI_DIS.description: Set this bit to disable accessing MSPI flash/MSPI ram by SYS AXI matrix during boot_mode_download.

DIS_TWAI.description: Represents whether TWAI function is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

JTAG_SEL_ENABLE.description: Represents whether the selection between usb_to_jtag and pad_to_jtag through strapping gpio15 when both EFUSE_DIS_PAD_JTAG and EFUSE_DIS_USB_JTAG are equal to 0 is enabled or disabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

SOFT_DIS_JTAG.description: Represents whether JTAG is disabled in soft way. Odd number: disabled. Even number: enabled.

DIS_PAD_JTAG.description: Represents whether JTAG is disabled in the hard way(permanently). 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

DIS_DOWNLOAD_MANUAL_ENCRYPT.description: Represents whether flash encrypt function is disabled or enabled(except in SPI boot mode). 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

USB_DEVICE_DREFH.description: USB intphy of usb device signle-end input high threshold, 1.76V to 2V. Step by 80mV

USB_OTG11_DREFH.description: USB intphy of usb otg11 signle-end input high threshold, 1.76V to 2V. Step by 80mV

KM_HUK_GEN_STATE_LOW.description: Set this bit to control validation of HUK generate mode. Odd of 1 is invalid, even of 1 is valid.

KM_HUK_GEN_STATE_HIGH.description: Set this bit to control validation of HUK generate mode. Odd of 1 is invalid, even of 1 is valid.

KM_RND_SWITCH_CYCLE.description: Set bits to control key manager random number switch cycle. 0: control by register. 1: 8 km clk cycles. 2: 16 km cycles. 3: 32 km cycles.

KM_DEPLOY_ONLY_ONCE.description: Set each bit to control whether corresponding key can only be deployed once. 1 is true, 0 is false. Bit0: ecdsa. Bit1: xts. Bit2: hmac. Bit3: ds.

FORCE_USE_KEY_MANAGER_KEY.description: Set each bit to control whether corresponding key must come from key manager.. 1 is true, 0 is false. Bit0: ecdsa. Bit1: xts. Bit2: hmac. Bit3: ds.

FORCE_DISABLE_SW_INIT_KEY.description: Set this bit to disable software written init key, and force use efuse_init_key.

XTS_KEY_LENGTH_256.description: Set this bit to configure flash encryption use xts-128 key, else use xts-256 key.

WDT_DELAY_SEL.description: Represents whether RTC watchdog timeout threshold is selected at startup. 1: selected. 0: not selected.

SPI_BOOT_CRYPT_CNT.description: Represents whether SPI boot encrypt/decrypt is disabled or enabled. Odd number of 1: enabled. Even number of 1: disabled.

SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE0.description: Represents whether revoking first secure boot key is enabled or disabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE1.description: Represents whether revoking second secure boot key is enabled or disabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE2.description: Represents whether revoking third secure boot key is enabled or disabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

SEC_DPA_LEVEL.description: Represents the spa secure level by configuring the clock random divide mode.

ECDSA_ENABLE_SOFT_K.description: Represents whether hardware random number k is forced used in ESDCA. 1: force used. 0: not force used.

CRYPT_DPA_ENABLE.description: Represents whether anti-dpa attack is enabled. 1:enabled. 0: disabled.

SECURE_BOOT_EN.description: Represents whether secure boot is enabled or disabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

SECURE_BOOT_AGGRESSIVE_REVOKE.description: Represents whether revoking aggressive secure boot is enabled or disabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

FLASH_TYPE.description: The type of interfaced flash. 0: four data lines, 1: eight data lines.

FLASH_ECC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable ecc for flash boot.

DIS_USB_OTG_DOWNLOAD_MODE.description: Set this bit to disable download via USB-OTG.

FLASH_TPUW.description: Represents the flash waiting time after power-up, in unit of ms. When the value less than 15, the waiting time is the programmed value. Otherwise, the waiting time is 2 times the programmed value.

DIS_DOWNLOAD_MODE.description: Represents whether Download mode is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

DIS_DIRECT_BOOT.description: Represents whether direct boot mode is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

DIS_USB_SERIAL_JTAG_ROM_PRINT.description: Represents whether print from USB-Serial-JTAG is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

DIS_USB_SERIAL_JTAG_DOWNLOAD_MODE.description: Represents whether the USB-Serial-JTAG download function is disabled or enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

ENABLE_SECURITY_DOWNLOAD.description: Represents whether security download is enabled or disabled. 1: enabled. 0: disabled.

UART_PRINT_CONTROL.description: Represents the type of UART printing. 00: force enable printing. 01: enable printing when GPIO8 is reset at low level. 10: enable printing when GPIO8 is reset at high level. 11: force disable printing.

FORCE_SEND_RESUME.description: Represents whether ROM code is forced to send a resume command during SPI boot. 1: forced. 0:not forced.

SECURE_VERSION.description: Represents the version used by ESP-IDF anti-rollback feature.

SECURE_BOOT_DISABLE_FAST_WAKE.description: Represents whether FAST VERIFY ON WAKE is disabled or enabled when Secure Boot is enabled. 1: disabled. 0: enabled.

HYS_EN_PAD.description: Represents whether the hysteresis function of corresponding PAD is enabled. 1: enabled. 0:disabled.

USB_DEVICE_DREFL.description: Represents the usb device single-end input low threhold, 0.8 V to 1.04 V with step of 80 mV.

USB_OTG11_DREFL.description: Represents the usb otg11 single-end input low threhold, 0.8 V to 1.04 V with step of 80 mV.

HP_PWR_SRC_SEL.description: HP system power source select. 0:LDO. 1: DCDC.

DIS_WDT.description: Set this bit to disable watch dog.

DIS_SWD.description: Set this bit to disable super-watchdog.

MAC_1.description: Stores the high 16 bits of MAC address.

MAC_EXT.description: Stores the extended bits of MAC address.

SYS_DATA_PART0_2.description: Stores the second 32 bits of the zeroth part of system data.

SYS_DATA_PART1_4.description: Stores the fourth 32 bits of the first part of system data.

SYS_DATA_PART1_5.description: Stores the fifth 32 bits of the first part of system data.

SYS_DATA_PART1_6.description: Stores the sixth 32 bits of the first part of system data.

SYS_DATA_PART1_7.description: Stores the seventh 32 bits of the first part of system data.

FRAME_START.description: Configures whether or not to start encoding one frame.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: Start encoding one frame

DMA_MOVE_START.description: Configures whether or not to start moving reference data from external mem.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: H264 start moving two MB lines of reference frame from external mem to internal mem

FRAME_MODE.description: Configures H264 running mode. When field H264_DUAL_STREAM_MODE is set to 1, this field must be set to 1 too.\\0: GOP mode. Before every GOP first frame start, need reconfig reference frame DMA\\1: Frame mode. Before every frame start, need reconfig reference frame DMA

SYS_RST_PULSE.description: Configures whether or not to reset H264 ip.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: Reset H264 ip

DUAL_STREAM_MODE.description: Configures whether or not to enable dual stream mode. When this field is set to 1,  H264_FRAME_MODE field must be set to 1 too.\\0: Normal mode\\1: Dual stream mode

GOP_NUM.description: Configures the frame number of one GOP.\\0: The frame number of one GOP is infinite\\Others: Actual frame number of one GOP

A_SYS_TOTAL_MB_Y.description: Configures video A vertical MB resolution.

A_SYS_TOTAL_MB_X.description: Configures video A horizontal MB resolution.

A_DB_TMP_READY_TRIGGER_MB_NUM.description: Configures when to trigger  video A H264_DB_TMP_READY_INT. When the (MB number of written db temp+1) is greater than this filed in first MB line, trigger H264_DB_TMP_READY_INT. Min is 3.

A_REC_READY_TRIGGER_MB_LINES.description: Configures when to trigger  video A H264_REC_READY_INT. When the MB line number of generated reconstruct pixel is greater than this filed, trigger H264_REC_READY_INT. Min is 4.

A_INTRA_COST_CMP_OFFSET.description: Configures video A intra cost offset when I MB compared with P MB.

A_C_DECI_SCORE.description: Configures video A chroma MB decimate score. When chroma score is smaller than it, chroma decimate will be enable.

A_L_DECI_SCORE.description: Configures video A luma MB decimate score. When luma score is smaller than it, luma decimate will be enable.
