REG_SCL_OE_FORCE_EN.description: This bit is used to force scl_oe

REG_DATA_BYTE_CNT_UNLATCH.description: 1: read current real-time updated value  0: read latch data byte cnt value

REG_MEM_CLK_FORCE_ON.description: 1: dev characteristic and address table memory clk  date force on . 0 :  clock gating by rd/wr.

REG_CMD_BUF_EMPTY_THLD.description: Command Buffer Empty Threshold Value is used to control the number of empty locations(or greater) in the Command Buffer that trigger CMD_BUFFER_READY_STAT interrupt.

REG_RESP_BUF_THLD.description: Response Buffer Threshold Value is used to control the number of entries in the Response Buffer that trigger the RESP_READY_STAT_INTR.

REG_IBI_DATA_BUF_THLD.description: In-Band Interrupt Data Threshold Value . Every In Band Interrupt received by I3C controller generates an IBI status. This field controls the number of IBI data entries in the IBI buffer that trigger the IBI_DATA_THLD_STAT interrupt.

REG_TX_DATA_BUF_THLD.description: Transmit Buffer Threshold Value. This field controls the number of empty locations in the Transmit FIFO that trigger the TX_THLD_STAT interrupt. Supports values: 000:2  001:4  010:8  011:16  100:31, else:31

REG_RX_DATA_BUF_THLD.description: Receive Buffer Threshold Value. This field controls the number of empty locations in the Receive FIFO that trigger the RX_THLD_STAT interrupt. Supports: 000:2  001:4  010:8  011:16  100:31, else:31

REG_NOTIFY_SIR_REJECTED.description: Notify Rejected Slave Interrupt Request Control. This bit is used to suppress reporting to the application about Slave Interrupt Request. 0:Suppress passing the IBI Status to the IBI FIFO(hence not notifying the application) when a SIR request is NACKed and auto-disabled base on the IBI_SIR_REQ_REJECT register. 1: Writes IBI Status to the IBI FIFO(hence notifying the application) when SIR request is NACKed and auto-disabled based on the IBI_SIR_REQ_REJECT registerl.

REG_SIR_REQ_REJECT.description: The application of controller can decide whether to send ACK or NACK for Slave request received from any I3C device. A device specific response control bit is provided to select the response option, Master will ACK/NACK the Master Request based on programming of control bit, corresponding to the interrupting device. 0:ACK the SIR Request  1:NACK and send direct auto disable CCC

TX_DATA_BUF_THLD_INT_ST.description: This interrupt is generated when number of empty locations in transmit buffer is greater than or equal to threshold value specified by TX_EMPTY_BUS_THLD field in DATA_BUFFER_THLD_CTRL register. This interrupt will be cleared automatically when number of empty locations in transmit buffer is less than threshold value.

RX_DATA_BUF_THLD_INT_ST.description: This interrupt is generated when number of entries in receive buffer is greater than or equal to threshold value specified by RX_BUF_THLD field in DATA_BUFFER_THLD_CTRL register. This interrupt will be cleared automatically when number of entries in receive buffer is less than threshold value.

IBI_STATUS_THLD_INT_ST.description: Only used in master mode. This interrupt is generated when number of entries in IBI buffer is greater than or equal to threshold value specified by IBI_BUF_THLD field in BUFFER_THLD_CTRL register. This interrupt will be cleared automatically when number of entries in IBI buffer is less than threshold value.

CMD_BUF_EMPTY_THLD_INT_ST.description: This interrupt is generated when number of empty locations in command buffer is greater than or equal to threshold value specified by CMD_EMPTY_BUF_THLD field in BUFFER_THLD_CTRL register. This interrupt will be cleared automatically when number of empty locations in command buffer is less than threshold value.

RESP_READY_INT_ST.description: This interrupt is generated when number of entries in response buffer is greater than or equal to threshold value specified by RESP_BUF_THLD field in BUFFER_THLD_CTRL register. This interrupt will be cleared automatically when number of entries in response buffer is less than threshold value.

NXT_CMD_REQ_ERR_INT_ST.description: This interrupt is generated if toc is 0(master will restart next command), but command buf is empty.

TRANSFER_ERR_INT_ST.description: This interrupt is generated if any error occurs during transfer. The error type will be specified in the response packet associated with the command (in ERR_STATUS field of RESPONSE_BUFFER_PORT register). This bit can be cleared by writing 1'h1.

IBI_STATUS_THLD_INT_ENA.description: Only used in master mode. IBI Buffer threshold status enable.

NXT_CMD_REQ_ERR_INT_ENA.description: next command request error status enable

CMD_BUF_EMPTY_CNT.description: Command Buffer Empty Locations contains the number of empty locations in the command buffer.

RESP_BUF_CNT.description: Response Buffer Level Value contains the number of valid data entries in the response buffer.

IBI_DATA_BUF_CNT.description: IBI Buffer Level Value contains the number of valid entries in the IBI Buffer. This is field is used in master mode.

IBI_STATUS_BUF_CNT.description: IBI Buffer Status Count contains the number of IBI status entries in the IBI Buffer. This field is used in master mode.

TX_DATA_BUF_EMPTY_CNT.description: Transmit Buffer Empty Level Value contains the number of empty locations in the transmit Buffer.

RX_DATA_BUF_CNT.description: Receive Buffer Level value contains the number of valid data entries in the receive buffer.

SDA_LVL.description: This bit is used to check the SCL line level to recover from error and  for debugging. This bit reflects the value of synchronized scl_in_a.

SCL_LVL.description: This bit is used to check the SDA line level to recover from error and  for debugging. This bit reflects the value of synchronized sda_in_a.

DAA_MODE_FSM_STATE.description: Reflects whether the Master Controller is in IDLE or not. This bit will be set when all the buffer(Command, Response, IBI, Transmit, Receive) are empty along with the Master State machine is in idle state. 0X0: not in idle  0x1: in idle

DATA_BYTE_CNT.description: Present transfer data byte cnt: tx data byte cnt if write  rx data byte cnt if read  ibi data byte cnt if IBI handle.

REG_I3C_MST_OD_LOW_PERIOD.description: SCL Open-Drain low count for I3C transfers targeted to I3C devices.

REG_I3C_MST_OD_HIGH_PERIOD.description: SCL Open-Drain High count for I3C transfers targeted to I3C devices.

REG_I2C_FM_HIGH_PERIOD.description: The SCL open-drain low count timing for I2C Fast Mode transfers.

REG_SDA_OD_SAMPLE_TIME.description: It is used to adjust sda sample point when scl high under open drain speed

REG_SDA_PP_SAMPLE_TIME.description: It is used to adjust sda sample point when scl high under push pull speed

REG_SDA_OD_TX_HOLD_TIME.description: It is used to adjust sda drive point after scl neg under open drain speed

REG_SDA_PP_TX_HOLD_TIME.description: It is used to adjust sda dirve point after scl neg under push pull speed

REG_BUS_FREE_TIME.description: I3C Bus Free Count Value. This field is used only in Master mode. In pure Bus System, this field represents tCAS.  In Mixed Bus System, this field is expected to be programmed to tLOW of I2C Timing.

REG_I3C_MST_VER_ID.description: This field indicates the controller current release number that is read by an application.

REG_I3C_MST_VER_TYPE.description: This field indicates the controller current release type that is read by an application.

REG_I3C_MST_FPGA_DEBUG_PROBE.description: For Debug Probe Test on FPGA

MCU_OE.description: Configures whether or not to enable the output of GPIOn in sleep mode. 0: Disable 1: Enable

SLP_SEL.description: Configures whether or not to enter sleep mode for GPIOn. 0: Not enter 1: Enter

MCU_WPD.description: Configure whether or not to enable pull-down resistor of GPIOn during sleep mode. 0: Disable 1: Enable

MCU_WPU.description: Configures whether or not to enable pull-up resistor of GPIOn during sleep mode. 0: Disable 1: Enable

MCU_IE.description: Configures whether or not to enable the input of GPIOn during sleep mode. 0: Disable 1: Enable

MCU_DRV.description: Configures the drive strength of GPIOn during sleep mode. 0: ~5 mA 1: ~10 mA 2: ~20 mA 3: ~40 mA

FUN_WPD.description: Configures whether or not to enable pull-down resistor of GPIOn. 0: Disable 1: Enable

FUN_WPU.description: Configures whether or not enable pull-up resistor of GPIOn. 0: Disable 1: Enable

FUN_IE.description: Configures whether or not to enable input of GPIOn. 0: Disable 1: Enable

FUN_DRV.description: Configures the drive strength of GPIOn. 0: ~5 mA 1: ~10 mA 2: ~20 mA 3: ~40 mA

MCU_SEL.description: Configures to select IO MUX function for this pin. 0: Select Function 0 1: Select Function 1 ......

FILTER_EN.description: Configures whether or not to enable filter for pin input signals. 0: Disable 1: Enable

BF_TAIL_PIXEN_PULSE_TH.description: matrix tail pixen high level threshold, must < hnum-1, only reg_bf_tail_pixen_pulse_th!=0 and reg_bf_tail_pixen_pulse_tl!=0 and reg_bf_tail_pixen_pulse_th < reg_bf_tail_pixen_pulse_tl will enable tail pulse function

BF_PADDING_DATA.description: this field configures bf matrix padding data

BF_PADDING_MODE.description: this bit configures the padding mode of bf matrix.  0: use pixel in image to do padding   1: use reg_padding_data to do padding

SIGMA.description: this field configures the bayer denoising level, valid data from 2 to 20

GAU_TEMPLATE21.description: this field configures index 21 of gausian template

GAU_TEMPLATE22.description: this field configures index 22 of gausian template

DYN_EN.description: this bit configures the dyn dpc enable. 0: disable, 1: enable

DPC_BLACK_EN.description: this bit configures input image type select when in check mode, 0: white img, 1: black img

DPC_METHOD_SEL.description: this bit configures dyn dpc method select. 0: simple method, 1: hard method

DPC_CHECK_OD_EN.description: this bit configures output pixel data when in check mode or not. 0: no data output, 1: data output

DPC_THRESHOLD_L.description: this bit configures the threshold to detect black img in check mode, or the low threshold(use 8 bit 0~255) in dyn method 0, or the low threshold factor (use 5 bit 10000-> 16/16, 00001->1/16, 0/16~16/16) in dyn method 1

DPC_THRESHOLD_H.description: this bit configures the threshold to detect white img in check mode, or the high threshold(use 8 bit 0~255) in dyn method 0, or the high threshold factor (use 5 bit 10000-> 16/16, 00001->1/16, 0/16~16/16) in dyn method 1

DPC_FACTOR_DARK.description: this field configures the dynamic correction method 1 dark   factor

DPC_FACTOR_BRIG.description: this field configures the dynamic correction method 1 bright factor

DPC_TAIL_PIXEN_PULSE_TL.description: matrix tail pixen low level threshold,  should not to large to prevent expanding to next frame, only reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_th!=0 and reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_tl!=0 and reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_th < reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_tl will enable tail pulse function

DPC_TAIL_PIXEN_PULSE_TH.description: matrix tail pixen high level threshold, must < hnum-1, only reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_th!=0 and reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_tl!=0 and reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_th < reg_dpc_tail_pixen_pulse_tl will enable tail pulse function

DPC_DEADPIX_CNT.description: this field represents the dead pixel count

AE_UPDATE.description: write 1 to this bit triggers one statistic event

SHARP_THRESHOLD_LOW.description: this field configures sharpen threshold for detail

SHARP_THRESHOLD_HIGH.description: this field configures sharpen threshold for edge

SHARP_AMOUNT_LOW.description: this field configures sharpen amount for detail

SHARP_AMOUNT_HIGH.description: this field configures sharpen amount for edge

SHARP_FILTER_COE00.description: this field configures unsharp masking(usm) filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE01.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE02.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE10.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE11.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE12.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE20.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE21.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_FILTER_COE22.description: this field configures usm filter coefficient

SHARP_TAIL_PIXEN_PULSE_TL.description: matrix tail pixen low level threshold,  should not to large to prevent expanding to next frame, only reg_demosaic_tail_pixen_pulse_th!=0 and reg_demosaic_tail_pixen_pulse_tl!=0 and reg_demosaic_tail_pixen_pulse_th < reg_demosaic_tail_pixen_pulse_tl will enable tail pulse function

SHARP_TAIL_PIXEN_PULSE_TH.description: matrix tail pixen high level threshold, must < hnum-1, only reg_sharp_tail_pixen_pulse_th!=0 and reg_sharp_tail_pixen_pulse_tl!=0 and reg_sharp_tail_pixen_pulse_th < reg_sharp_tail_pixen_pulse_tl will enable tail pulse function

SHARP_PADDING_DATA.description: this field configures sharp padding data

SHARP_PADDING_MODE.description: this field configures sharp padding mode

SHARP_GRADIENT_MAX.description: this field configures sharp max gradient, refresh at the end of each frame end

DMA_EN.description: write 1 to triger dma to get 1 frame

DMA_DATA_TYPE.description: this field configures the idi data type for image data

DMA_BURST_LEN.description: this field configures dma burst len when data source is dma. set according to dma_msize, it is the number of 64bits in a dma transfer

DMA_INTERVAL.description: this field configures dma req interval, 12'b1: 1 cycle, 12'b11 2 cycle ...

DMA_RAW_NUM_TOTAL.description: this field configures the the number of 64bits in a frame

CAM_EN.description: write 1 to start recive camera data, write 0 to disable

CAM_RESET.description: this bit configures cam clk domain reset, 1: reset cam input logic, 0: release reset

CAM_CLK_INV.description: this bit configures the invertion of cam clk from pad. 0: not invert cam clk, 1: invert cam clk

CAM_DATA_ORDER.description: this field configures data order of cam port, 0: cam_data_in, 1:{cam_data_in[7:0], cam_data_in[15:8]}

CAM_2BYTE_MODE.description: this field configures enable of cam 2 byte mode(input 2 bytes each clock). 0: disable, 1: enable

CAM_DATA_TYPE.description: this field configures idi data type for image data, 0x2a: RAW8, 0x2b: RAW10, 0x2c: RAW12

CAM_DE_INV.description: this bit configures cam data enable invert. 0: not invert, 1: invert

CAM_HSYNC_INV.description: this bit configures cam hsync invert. 0: not invert, 1: invert

CAM_VSYNC_INV.description: this bit configures cam vsync invert. 0: not invert, 1: invert

CAM_VSYNC_FILTER_THRES.description: this bit configures the number of clock of vsync filter length

CAM_VSYNC_FILTER_EN.description: this bit configures vsync filter en

AF_AUTO_UPDATE.description: this bit configures auto_update enable. when set to 1, will update sum and lum each frame

AF_MANUAL_UPDATE.description: write 1 to this bit will update the sum and lum once

AF_ENV_THRESHOLD.description: this field configures env threshold. when both sum and lum changes larger than this value, consider environment changes and need to trigger a new autofocus. 4Bit fractional

AF_ENV_PERIOD.description: this field configures environment changes detection period (frame). When set to 0, disable this function

AF_THPIXNUM.description: this field configures pixnum used when calculating the autofocus threshold. Set to 0 to disable threshold calculation

AF_GEN_THRESHOLD_MIN.description: this field configures min threshold when use auto_threshold

AF_GEN_THRESHOLD_MAX.description: this field configures max threshold when use auto_threshold

AF_ENV_USER_THRESHOLD_SUM.description: this field configures user setup env detect sum threshold

AF_ENV_USER_THRESHOLD_LUM.description: this field configures user setup env detect lum threshold

AF_THRESHOLD.description: this field configures user threshold. When set to non-zero, autofocus will use this threshold

AF_GEN_THRESHOLD.description: this field represents the last calculated threshold

AF_RPOINT_A.description: this field configures left coordinate of focus window a, must >= 2

AF_LPOINT_A.description: this field configures top coordinate of focus window a, must >= 2

AF_BPOINT_A.description: this field configures right coordinate of focus window a, must <= hnum-2

AF_TPOINT_A.description: this field configures bottom coordinate of focus window a, must <= hnum-2

AF_RPOINT_B.description: this field configures left coordinate of focus window b, must >= 2

AF_LPOINT_B.description: this field configures top coordinate of focus window b, must >= 2

AF_BPOINT_B.description: this field configures right coordinate of focus window b, must <= hnum-2

AF_TPOINT_B.description: this field configures bottom coordinate of focus window b, must <= hnum-2

AF_RPOINT_C.description: this field configures left coordinate of focus window c, must >= 2

AF_LPOINT_C.description: this field configures top coordinate of focus window c, must >= 2

AF_BPOINT_C.description: this field configures right coordinate of focus window c, must <= hnum-2

AF_TPOINT_C.description: this field configures bottom coordinate of focus window c, must <= hnum-2

AF_SUMA.description: this field represents the result of accumulation of pix grad of focus window a

AF_SUMB.description: this field represents the result of accumulation of pix grad of focus window b

AF_SUMC.description: this field represents the result of accumulation of pix grad of focus window c

AF_LUMA.description: this field represents the result of accumulation of pix light of focus window a

AF_LUMB.description: this field represents the result of accumulation of pix light of focus window b

AF_LUMC.description: this field represents the result of accumulation of pix light of focus window c

AWB_MODE.description: this field configures awb algo sel. 00: none sellected. 01: sel algo0. 10: sel algo1. 11: sel both algo0 and algo1

AWB_SAMPLE.description: this bit configures awb sample location, 0:before ccm, 1:after ccm

AWB_RPOINT.description: this field configures awb window right coordinate

AWB_LPOINT.description: this field configures awb window left coordinate

AWB_BPOINT.description: this field configures awb window bottom coordinate

AWB_TPOINT.description: this field configures awb window top coordinate

AWB_MIN_LUM.description: this field configures lower threshold of r+g+b

AWB_MAX_LUM.description: this field configures upper threshold of r+g+b

AWB_MIN_RG.description: this field configures lower threshold of r/g, 2bit integer and 8bit fraction

AWB_MAX_RG.description: this field configures upper threshold of r/g, 2bit integer and 8bit fraction

AWB_MIN_BG.description: this field configures lower threshold of b/g, 2bit integer and 8bit fraction

AWB_MAX_BG.description: this field configures upper threshold of b/g, 2bit integer and 8bit fraction

AWB0_WHITE_CNT.description: this field configures number of white point detected of algo0

AWB0_ACC_R.description: this field represents accumulate of channel r of all white point of algo0

AWB0_ACC_G.description: this field represents accumulate of channel g of all white point of algo0

AWB0_ACC_B.description: this field represents accumulate of channel b of all white point of algo0

COLOR_SATURATION.description: this field configures the color saturation value

COLOR_HUE.description: this field configures the color hue angle

COLOR_CONTRAST.description: this field configures the color contrast value

COLOR_BRIGHTNESS.description: this field configures the color brightness value, signed 2's complement

BLC_R3_VALUE.description: this field configures the black level of bottom right channel of bayer img

BLC_R2_VALUE.description: this field configures the black level of bottom left channel of bayer img

BLC_R1_VALUE.description: this field configures the black level of top right channel of bayer img

BLC_R0_VALUE.description: this field configures the black level of top left channel of bayer img

BLC_R3_STRETCH.description: this bit configures the stretch feature of bottom right channel. 0: stretch disable, 1: stretch enable

BLC_R2_STRETCH.description: this bit configures the stretch feature of bottom left channel. 0: stretch disable, 1: stretch enable

BLC_R1_STRETCH.description: this bit configures the stretch feature of top right channel. 0: stretch disable, 1: stretch enable

BLC_R0_STRETCH.description: this bit configures the stretch feature of top left channel. 0: stretch disable, 1: stretch enable

BLC_WINDOW_TOP.description: this field configures blc average calculation window top

BLC_WINDOW_LEFT.description: this field configures blc average calculation window left

BLC_WINDOW_VNUM.description: this field configures blc average calculation window vnum

BLC_WINDOW_HNUM.description: this field configures blc average calculation window hnum

BLC_FILTER_EN.description: this bit configures enable blc average input filter. 0: disable, 1: enable

YUV_MODE.description: this bit configures the yuv mode. 0: ITU-R BT.601, 1: ITU-R BT.709

YUV_RANGE.description: this bit configures the yuv range. 0: full range, 1: limit range

JPEG_START.description: start to compress a new pic(in dma reg mode)

DEBUG_DIRECT_OUT_EN.description: 0:normal mode,1:debug mode for direct output from input

GRAY_SEL.description: 0:use non-fifo way to access qnr ram,1:use fifo way to access qnr ram

DHT_FIFO_EN.description: 0:use non-fifo way to write dht len_total/codemin/value table,1:use fifo way to write dht len_total/codemin/value table. Reading dht len_total/codemin/value table only has nonfifo way

JFIF_VER.description: decode pause period to trigger decode_timeout int, the timeout periods =2 power (reg_decode_timeout_thres) -1

DECODE_TIMEOUT_TASK_SEL.description: 0: software use reset to abort decode process ,1: decoder abort decode process by itself

SOFT_RST.description: when set to 1, soft reset JPEG module except jpeg_reg module

TAILER_EN.description: set this bit to add EOI of "0xffd9" at the end of bitstream

PAUSE_EN.description: set this bit to pause jpeg encoding

MEM_FORCE_PD.description: 0: no operation,1:force jpeg memory to power down

MEM_FORCE_PU.description: 0: no operation,1:force jpeg memory to power up

T0_DQT_INFO.description: Configure dqt table0's quantization coefficient precision in bit[7:4], configure dqt table0's table id in bit[3:0]

T1_DQT_INFO.description: Configure dqt table1's quantization coefficient precision in bit[7:4], configure dqt table1's table id in bit[3:0]

T2_DQT_INFO.description: Configure dqt table2's quantization coefficient precision in bit[7:4], configure dqt table2's table id in bit[3:0]

T3_DQT_INFO.description: Configure dqt table3's quantization coefficient precision in bit[7:4], configure dqt table3's table id in bit[3:0]

VA.description: configure picture's height. when encode, the max configurable bits is 14, when decode, the max configurable bits is 16

HA.description: configure picture's width. when encode, the max configurable bits is 14, when decode, the max configurable bits is 16

T0_QNR_VAL.description: write this reg to configure 64 quantization coefficient in t0 table

CHROMINANCE_QNR_VAL.description: write this reg to configure 64 quantization coefficient in t1 table

T2_QNR_VAL.description: write this reg to configure 64 quantization coefficient in t2 table

T3_QNR_VAL.description: write this reg to configure 64 quantization coefficient in t3 table

RESTART_INTERVAL.description: configure restart interval in DRI marker when decode

COMPONENT_NUM.description: configure number of components in frame when decode

SOS_CHECK_BYTE_NUM.description: Configure the byte number to check next sos marker in the multi-scan picture after one scan is decoded down. The real check number is reg_sos_check_byte_num+1

RST_CHECK_BYTE_NUM.description: Configure the byte number to check next rst marker after one rst interval is decoded down. The real check number is reg_rst_check_byte_num+1

DONE_INT_RAW.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when JPEG finishes encoding a picture..

RLE_PARALLEL_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that rle parallel error when decoding.

CID_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that scan id check with component fails when decoding.

C_DHT_DC_ID_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that scan component's dc dht id check with dc dht table's id fails when decoding.

C_DHT_AC_ID_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that scan component's ac dht id check with ac dht table's id fails when decoding.

C_DQT_ID_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that scan component's dqt id check with dqt table's id fails when decoding.

RST_UXP_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that RST header marker is detected but restart interval is 0 when decoding.

RST_CHECK_NONE_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that RST header marker is not detected but restart interval is not 0 when decoding.

RST_CHECK_POS_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that RST header marker position mismatches with restart interval when decoding.

OUT_EOF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last pixel of one square has been transmitted for Tx channel.

SR_COLOR_MODE_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that the selected source color mode is not supported.

DCT_DONE_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that one dct calculation is finished.

BS_LAST_BLOCK_EOF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that the coding process for last block is finished.

SCAN_CHECK_POS_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that SOS header marker position wrong when decoding.

UXP_DET_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that unsupported header marker is detected when decoding.

EN_FRAME_EOF_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that received pixel blocks are smaller than expected when encoding.

EN_FRAME_EOF_LACK_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that the frame eof sign bit from dma input is missing when encoding. But the number of pixel blocks is enough.

DE_FRAME_EOF_LACK_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that the either frame eof from dma input or eoi marker is missing when encoding. But the number of decoded blocks is enough.

MARKER_ERR_OTHER_SCAN_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that the following scans but not the first scan have header marker error when decoding.

UNDET_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that JPEG format is not detected at the eof data of a packet when decoding.

DECODE_TIMEOUT_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit to sign that decode pause time is longer than the setting decode timeout time when decoding.

BITSTREAM_EOF_VLD_CNT.description: the valid bit count for last bitstream

DCTOUT_ZZSCAN_ADDR.description: the zig-zag read addr from dctout_ram

QNRVAL_ZZSCAN_ADDR.description: the zig-zag read addr from qnrval_ram

LAST_BLOCK.description: indicate the encoding process for the last mcu of the picture

LAST_MCU.description: indicate the encoding process for the last block of the picture

LAST_DC.description: indicate the encoding process is at the header of the last block of the picture

PACKFIFO_READY.description: the jpeg pack_fifo ready signal, high active

YO.description: component y transferred from rgb input

Y_READY.description: component y valid signal, high active

CBO.description: component cb transferred from rgb input

CB_READY.description: component cb valid signal, high active

CRO.description: component cr transferred from rgb input

CR_READY.description: component cr valid signal, high active

HFM_BITSTREAM.description: the hufman bitstream during encoding process

DHT_TOTLEN_DC0.description: write the numbers of 1~n codeword length sum from 1~16 of dc0 table

DHT_VAL_DC0.description: write codeword corresponding huffman values of dc0 table

DHT_TOTLEN_AC0.description: write the numbers of 1~n codeword length sum from 1~16 of ac0 table

DHT_VAL_AC0.description: write codeword corresponding huffman values of ac0 table

DHT_TOTLEN_DC1.description: write the numbers of 1~n codeword length sum from 1~16 of dc1 table

DHT_VAL_DC1.description: write codeword corresponding huffman values of dc1 table

DHT_TOTLEN_AC1.description: write the numbers of 1~n codeword length sum from 1~16 of ac1 table

DHT_VAL_AC1.description: write codeword corresponding huffman values of ac1 table

DHT_CODEMIN_DC0.description: write the minimum codeword of  code length from 1~16 of dc0 table. The codeword is left shifted to the MSB position of a 16bit word

DHT_CODEMIN_AC0.description: write the minimum codeword of  code length from 1~16 of ac0 table. The codeword is left shifted to the MSB position of a 16bit word

DHT_CODEMIN_DC1.description: write the minimum codeword of  code length from 1~16 of dc1 table. The codeword is left shifted to the MSB position of a 16bit word

DHT_CODEMIN_AC1.description: write the minimum codeword of  code length from 1~16 of ac1 table. The codeword is left shifted to the MSB position of a 16bit word

CLK_EN.description: Reserved

LC_DMA_INT_RAW.description: LCDCAM interrupt raw register, valid in level.

LCD_CK_IDLE_EDGE.description: 1: LCD_PCLK line is high when idle     0: LCD_PCLK line is low when idle.

LCD_CK_OUT_EDGE.description: 1: LCD_PCLK line is high in the first half data cycle.     0: LCD_PCLK line is low in the second half data cycle.

LCD_CLK_SEL.description: Select LCD module source clock. 0: no clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: no clock.

CLK_EN.description: Set this bit to enable clk gate

CAM_STOP_EN.description: Camera stop enable signal, 1: camera stops when DMA Rx FIFO is full. 0: Not stop.

CAM_VSYNC_FILTER_THRES.description: Filter threshold value for CAM_VSYNC signal.

CAM_UPDATE.description: 1: Update Camera registers, will be cleared by hardware. 0 : Not care.

CAM_BYTE_ORDER.description: 1: Change data bit order, change CAM_DATA_in[7:0] to CAM_DATA_in[0:7] in one byte mode, and bits[15:0] to bits[0:15] in two byte mode.  0: Not change.

CAM_BIT_ORDER.description: 1: invert data byte order, only valid in 2 byte mode. 0: Not change.

CAM_VS_EOF_EN.description: 1: CAM_VSYNC to generate in_suc_eof. 0: in_suc_eof is controlled by reg_cam_rec_data_cyclelen.

CAM_CLK_SEL.description: Select Camera module source clock. 0: no clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: no clock.

CAM_REC_DATA_BYTELEN.description: Camera receive data byte length minus 1 to set DMA in_suc_eof_int.

CAM_LINE_INT_NUM.description: The line number minus 1 to generate cam_hs_int.

CAM_CLK_INV.description: 1: Invert  the input signal CAM_PCLK. 0: Not invert.

CAM_2BYTE_EN.description: 1: The bit number of input data is 9~16.  0: The bit number of input data is 0~8.

CAM_DE_INV.description: CAM_DE invert enable signal, valid in high level.

CAM_HSYNC_INV.description: CAM_HSYNC invert enable signal, valid in high level.

CAM_VSYNC_INV.description: CAM_VSYNC invert enable signal, valid in high level.

CAM_VH_DE_MODE_EN.description: 1: Input control signals are CAM_DE CAM_HSYNC and CAM_VSYNC. 0: Input control signals are CAM_DE and CAM_VSYNC.

CAM_CONV_YUV2YUV_MODE.description: 0: to yuv422. 1: to yuv420. 2: to yuv411. 3: disabled.  To enable yuv2yuv mode, trans_mode must be set to 1.

CAM_CONV_YUV_MODE.description: 0: yuv422. 1: yuv420. 2: yuv411. When in yuv2yuv mode, yuv_mode decides the yuv mode of Data_in

CAM_CONV_DATA_OUT_MODE.description: LIMIT or FULL mode of Data out. 0: limit. 1: full

CAM_CONV_DATA_IN_MODE.description: LIMIT or FULL mode of Data in. 0: limit. 1: full

CAM_CONV_TRANS_MODE.description: 0: YUV to RGB. 1: RGB to YUV.

LCD_CONV_TXTORX.description: 0: txtorx mode off. 1: txtorx mode on.

LCD_CONV_YUV2YUV_MODE.description: 0: to yuv422. 1: to yuv420. 2: to yuv411. 3: disabled.  To enable yuv2yuv mode, trans_mode must be set to 1.

LCD_CONV_YUV_MODE.description: 0: yuv422. 1: yuv420. 2: yuv411. When in yuv2yuv mode, yuv_mode decides the yuv mode of Data_in

LCD_CONV_DATA_OUT_MODE.description: LIMIT or FULL mode of Data out. 0: limit. 1: full

LCD_CONV_DATA_IN_MODE.description: LIMIT or FULL mode of Data in. 0: limit. 1: full

LCD_CONV_TRANS_MODE.description: 0: YUV to RGB. 1: RGB to YUV.

LCD_DOUT_CYCLELEN.description: The output data cycles minus 1 of LCD module.

LCD_ALWAYS_OUT_EN.description: LCD always output when LCD is in LCD_DOUT state, unless reg_lcd_start is cleared or reg_lcd_reset is set.

LCD_DOUT_BIT_ORDER.description: 1: change bit order in every byte. 0: Not change.

LCD_UPDATE.description: 1: Update LCD registers, will be cleared by hardware. 0 : Not care.

LCD_BIT_ORDER.description: 1: Change data bit order, change LCD_DATA_out[7:0] to LCD_DATA_out[0:7] in one byte mode, and bits[15:0] to bits[0:15] in two byte mode.  0: Not change.

LCD_BYTE_ORDER.description: 1: invert data byte order, only valid in 2 byte mode. 0: Not change.

LCD_DOUT.description: 1: Be able to send data out in LCD sequence when LCD starts. 0: Disable.

LCD_DUMMY.description: 1: Enable DUMMY phase in LCD sequence when LCD starts. 0: Disable.

LCD_CMD.description: 1: Be able to send command in LCD sequence when LCD starts. 0: Disable.

LCD_START.description: LCD start sending data enable signal, valid in high level.

LCD_CMD_2_CYCLE_EN.description: The cycle length of command phase. 1: 2 cycles. 0: 1 cycle.

LCD_WIRE_MODE.description: The wire width of LCD output. 0: 8bit. 1: 16bit 2: 24bit

LCD_VFK_CYCLELEN.description: The setup cycle length minus 1 in LCD non-RGB mode.

LCD_VBK_CYCLELEN.description: The vertical back blank region cycle length minus 1 in LCD RGB mode, or the hold time cycle length in LCD non-RGB mode.

LCD_NEXT_FRAME_EN.description: 1: Send the next frame data when the current frame is sent out. 0: LCD stops when the current frame is sent out.

LCD_BK_EN.description: 1: Enable blank region when LCD sends data out. 0: No blank region.

LCD_CD_DATA_SET.description: 1: LCD_CD = !reg_cd_idle_edge when lcd_st[2:0] is in LCD_DOUT state.  0: LCD_CD = reg_cd_idle_edge.

LCD_CD_DUMMY_SET.description: 1: LCD_CD = !reg_cd_idle_edge when lcd_st[2:0] is in LCD_DUMMY state.  0: LCD_CD = reg_cd_idle_edge.

LCD_CD_CMD_SET.description: 1: LCD_CD = !reg_cd_idle_edge when lcd_st[2:0] is in LCD_CMD state.  0: LCD_CD = reg_cd_idle_edge.

LCD_HB_FRONT.description: It is the horizontal blank front porch of a frame.

LCD_VA_HEIGHT.description: It is the vertical active height of a frame.

LCD_VT_HEIGHT.description: It is the vertical total height of a frame.

LCD_RGB_MODE_EN.description: 1: Enable LCD RGB mode. 0: Disable LCD RGB mode.

LCD_VB_FRONT.description: It is the vertical blank front porch of a frame.

LCD_HA_WIDTH.description: It is the horizontal active width of a frame.

LCD_HT_WIDTH.description: It is the horizontal total width of a frame.

LCD_VSYNC_WIDTH.description: It is the position of LCD_VSYNC active pulse in a line.

LCD_VSYNC_IDLE_POL.description: It is the idle value of LCD_VSYNC.

LCD_DE_IDLE_POL.description: It is the idle value of LCD_DE.

LCD_HS_BLANK_EN.description: 1: The pulse of LCD_HSYNC is out in vertical blanking lines RGB mode. 0: LCD_HSYNC pulse is valid only in active region lines in RGB mode.

LCD_HSYNC_WIDTH.description: It is the position of LCD_HSYNC active pulse in a line.

LCD_HSYNC_IDLE_POL.description: It is the idle value of LCD_HSYNC.

LCD_HSYNC_POSITION.description: It is the position of LCD_HSYNC active pulse in a line.

LCD_FIRST_CMD_VALUE.description: The LCD write command value of first cmd cycle.

LCD_LATTER_CMD_VALUE.description: The LCD write command value of latter cmd cycle.

CH%s_DUTY.description: Initial duty cycle register for channel %s

CH%s_DUTY_R.description: Current duty cycle register for channel %s

EVT_TASK_EN0.description: Ledc event task enable bit register0.

EVT_TASK_EN1.description: Ledc event task enable bit register1.

EVT_TASK_EN2.description: Ledc event task enable bit register2.

TIMER%s_CNT_CAP.description: Ledc timer%s captured count value register.

TIMER_SEL_CH.description: Configures which timer is channel %s selected.\\0: Select timer0\\1: Select timer1\\2: Select timer2\\3: Select timer3

SIG_OUT_EN_CH.description: Configures whether or not to enable signal output on channel %s.\\0: Signal output disable\\1: Signal output enable

IDLE_LV_CH.description: Configures the output value when channel %s is inactive. Valid only when  LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s is 0.\\0: Output level is low\\1: Output level is high

PARA_UP_CH.description: Configures whether or not to update LEDC_HPOINT_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_START_CH%s, LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s, LEDC_TIMER_SEL_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_NUM_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_SCALE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_INC_CH%s, and LEDC_OVF_CNT_EN_CH%s fields for channel %s, and will be automatically cleared by hardware.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: Update

OVF_NUM_CH.description: Configures the maximum times of overflow minus 1.The LEDC_OVF_CNT_CH%s_INT interrupt will be triggered when channel %s overflows for (LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH%s + 1) times.

OVF_CNT_EN_CH.description: Configures whether or not to enable the ovf_cnt of channel %s.\\0: Disable\\1: Enable

OVF_CNT_RESET_CH.description: Configures whether or not to reset the  ovf_cnt of channel %s.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: Reset the ovf_cnt

HPOINT_CH.description: Configures high point of signal output on channel %s. The output value changes to high when the selected timers has reached the value specified by this register.

DUTY_CH.description: Configures the duty of signal output on channel %s.

DUTY_START_CH.description: Configures whether the duty cycle fading configurations take effect.\\0: Not take effect\\1: Take effect

DUTY_CH_R.description: Represents the current duty of output signal on channel %s.

TIMER_DUTY_RES.description: Configures the range of the counter in timer %s.

CLK_DIV_TIMER.description: Configures the divisor for the divider in timer %s.The least significant eight bits represent the fractional part.

TIMER_PAUSE.description: Configures whether or not to pause the counter in timer %s.\\0: Normal\\1: Pause

TIMER_RST.description: Configures whether or not to reset timer %s. The counter will show 0 after reset.\\0: Not reset\\1: Reset

TICK_SEL_TIMER.description: Configures which clock is timer %s selected. Unused.

TIMER_PARA_UP.description: Configures whether or not to update LEDC_CLK_DIV_TIMER%s and LEDC_TIMER%s_DUTY_RES.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: Update

TIMER_CNT.description: Represents the current counter value of timer %s.

MEM_TX_STATUS.description: Tx-SRAM write and read offset address.

MEM_RX_STATUS.description: Rx-SRAM write and read offset address.

RXFIFO_RD_BYTE.description: UART 0 accesses FIFO via this register.

RXFIFO_FULL_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than what rxfifo_full_thrhd specifies.

TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in Tx-FIFO is less than what txfifo_empty_thrhd specifies .

PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error in the data.

FRM_ERR_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error .

RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than the FIFO can store.

DSR_CHG_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of DSRn signal.

CTS_CHG_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of CTSn signal.

BRK_DET_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a 0 after the stop bit.

RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver takes more time than rx_tout_thrhd to receive a byte.

SW_XON_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver recevies Xon char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

SW_XOFF_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives Xoff char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a glitch in the middle of a start bit.

TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter completes  sending  NULL characters after all data in Tx-FIFO are sent.

TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has kept the shortest duration after sending the  last data.

TX_DONE_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has send out all data in FIFO.

AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the configured at_cmd char.

WAKEUP_INT_RAW.description: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when input rxd edge changes more times than what reg_active_threshold specifies in light sleeping mode.

CLKDIV.description: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

CLKDIV_FRAG.description: The decimal part of the frequency divider factor.

GLITCH_FILT.description: when input pulse width is lower than this value the pulse is ignored.

GLITCH_FILT_EN.description: Set this bit to enable Rx signal filter.

RXFIFO_CNT.description: Stores the byte number of valid data in Rx-FIFO.

DSRN.description: The register represent the level value of the internal uart dsr signal.

CTSN.description: This register represent the level value of the internal uart cts signal.

RXD.description: This register represent the  level value of the internal uart rxd signal.

TXFIFO_CNT.description: Stores the byte number of data in Tx-FIFO.

DTRN.description: This bit represents the level of the internal uart dtr signal.

RTSN.description: This bit represents the level of the internal uart rts signal.

TXD.description: This bit represents the  level of the internal uart txd signal.

PARITY.description: This register is used to configure the parity check mode.

PARITY_EN.description: Set this bit to enable uart parity check.

BIT_NUM.description: This register is used to set the length of data.

STOP_BIT_NUM.description: This register is used to set the length of  stop bit.

TXD_BRK.description: Set this bit to enbale transmitter to  send NULL when the process of sending data is done.

LOOPBACK.description: Set this bit to enable uart loopback test mode.

TX_FLOW_EN.description: Set this bit to enable flow control function for transmitter.

RXD_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

TXD_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

DIS_RX_DAT_OVF.description: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

ERR_WR_MASK.description: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

MEM_CLK_EN.description: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

SW_RTS.description: This register is used to configure the software rts signal which is used in software flow control.

RXFIFO_RST.description: Set this bit to reset the uart receive-FIFO.

TXFIFO_RST.description: Set this bit to reset the uart transmit-FIFO.

RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD.description: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD.description: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

CTS_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

DSR_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

RTS_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

DTR_INV.description: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

SW_DTR.description: This register is used to configure the software dtr signal which is used in software flow control.

CLK_EN.description: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

RX_FLOW_THRHD.description: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

RX_FLOW_EN.description: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

WK_CHAR1.description: This register restores the specified wake up char1 to wake up

WK_CHAR2.description: This register restores the specified wake up char2 to wake up

WK_CHAR3.description: This register restores the specified wake up char3 to wake up

WK_CHAR4.description: This register restores the specified wake up char4 to wake up

WK_CHAR0.description: This register restores the specified char0 to wake up

ACTIVE_THRESHOLD.description: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

RX_WAKE_UP_THRHD.description: In wake up mode 1 this field is used to set the received data number threshold to wake up chip.

WK_CHAR_NUM.description: This register is used to select number of wake up char.

WK_CHAR_MASK.description: This register is used to mask  wake up char.

WK_MODE_SEL.description: This register is used to select wake up mode. 0: RXD toggling to wake up. 1: received data number larger than

XON_CHAR.description: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

XOFF_CHAR.description: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

XON_XOFF_STILL_SEND.description: In software flow control mode, UART Tx is disabled once UART Rx receives XOFF. In this status, UART Tx can not transmit XOFF even the received data number is larger than UART_XOFF_THRESHOLD. Set this bit to enable UART Tx can transmit XON/XOFF when UART Tx is disabled.

SW_FLOW_CON_EN.description: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

XONOFF_DEL.description: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

FORCE_XON.description: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

FORCE_XOFF.description: Set this bit to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

SEND_XON.description: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

SEND_XOFF.description: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

XON_THRESHOLD.description: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xon char.

XOFF_THRESHOLD.description: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xoff char.

TX_BRK_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

RX_IDLE_THRHD.description: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

TX_IDLE_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

DL0_EN.description: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

DL1_EN.description: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

PRE_IDLE_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

POST_IDLE_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

RX_GAP_TOUT.description: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

AT_CMD_CHAR.description: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

CHAR_NUM.description: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

MEM_FORCE_PD.description: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

MEM_FORCE_PU.description: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

RX_TOUT_EN.description: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS.description: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

RX_TOUT_THRHD.description: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

TX_SRAM_WADDR.description: This register stores the offset write address in Tx-SRAM.

TX_SRAM_RADDR.description: This register stores the offset read address in Tx-SRAM.

RX_SRAM_RADDR.description: This register stores the offset read address in RX-SRAM.

RX_SRAM_WADDR.description: This register stores the offset write address in Rx-SRAM.

ST_URX_OUT.description: This is the status register of receiver.

ST_UTX_OUT.description: This is the status register of transmitter.

TX_SCLK_EN.description: Set this bit to enable UART Tx clock.

RX_SCLK_EN.description: Set this bit to enable UART Rx clock.

TX_RST_CORE.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset UART Tx.

RX_RST_CORE.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset UART Rx.

TX_AFIFO_FULL.description: Full signal of APB TX AFIFO.

TX_AFIFO_EMPTY.description: Empty signal of APB TX AFIFO.

RX_AFIFO_FULL.description: Full signal of APB RX AFIFO.

RX_AFIFO_EMPTY.description: Empty signal of APB RX AFIFO.

REG_UPDATE.description: Software write 1 would synchronize registers into UART Core clock domain and would be cleared by hardware after synchronization is done.

ID.description: This register is used to configure the uart_id.

RX_MODE_CFG.description: Parallel RX Sampling mode configuration register.

INT_ENA.description: Parallel IO interrupt enable singal configuration register.

INT_RAW.description: Parallel IO interrupt raw singal status register.

INT_ST.description: Parallel IO interrupt singal status register.

INT_CLR.description: Parallel IO interrupt  clear singal configuration register.

RX_CLK_CFG.description: Parallel IO RX clk configuration register

TX_CLK_CFG.description: Parallel IO TX clk configuration register

RX_EXT_EN_SEL.description: Configures rx external enable signal selection from IO PAD.

RX_SW_EN.description: Set this bit to enable data sampling by software.

RX_EXT_EN_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the external enable signal.

RX_PULSE_SUBMODE_SEL.description:
Configures the rxd pulse sampling submode. 
4'd0: positive pulse start(data bit included) &&  positive pulse end(data bit included)
4'd1: positive pulse start(data bit included) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
4'd2: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit included)
4'd3: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
4'd4: positive pulse start(data bit included) && length end
4'd5: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && length end

RX_SMP_MODE_SEL.description:
Configures the rxd sampling mode. 
2'b00: external level enable mode
2'b01: external pulse enable mode  
2'b10: internal software enable mode

RX_BITLEN.description: Configures expected byte number of received data.

RX_DATA_ORDER_INV.description: Set this bit to invert bit order of one byte sent from RX_FIFO to DMA.

RX_BUS_WID_SEL.description:
Configures the rxd bus width. 
3'd0: bus width is 1.
3'd1: bus width is 2.
3'd2: bus width is 4.
3'd3: bus width is 8.

RX_GATING_EN.description: Set this bit to enable the clock gating of output rx clock.

RX_TIMEOUT_EN.description: Set this bit to enable timeout function to generate error eof.

RX_EOF_GEN_SEL.description: Configures the DMA eof generated mechanism. 1'b0: eof generated by data bit length. 1'b1: eof generated by external enable signal.

RX_START.description: Set this bit to start rx data sampling.

TX_BITLEN.description: Configures expected byte number of sent data.

TX_DATA_ORDER_INV.description: Set this bit to invert bit order of one byte sent from TX_FIFO to IO data.

TX_BUS_WID_SEL.description:
Configures the txd bus width. 
3'd0: bus width is 1.
3'd1: bus width is 2.
3'd2: bus width is 4.
3'd3: bus width is 8.

TX_START.description: Set this bit to start tx data transmit.

TX_EOF_GEN_SEL.description: Configures the tx eof generated mechanism. 1'b0: eof generated by data bit length. 1'b1: eof generated by DMA eof.

TX_IDLE_VALUE.description: Configures bus value of transmitter in IDLE state.

TX_GATING_EN.description: Set this bit to enable the clock gating of output tx clock.

TX_VALID_OUTPUT_EN.description: Set this bit to enable the output of tx data valid signal.

TX_FIFO_SRST.description: Set this bit to reset async fifo in tx module.

RX_FIFO_SRST.description: Set this bit to reset async fifo in rx module.

RX_REG_UPDATE.description: Set this bit to update rx register configuration.

TX_READY.description: Represents the status that tx is ready to transmit.

TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT.

RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT.

TX_EOF_INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable TX_EOF_INT.

TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt status of TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT.

RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt status of RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT.

TX_EOF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt status of TX_EOF_INT.

TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT_ST.description: The masked interrupt status of TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT.

RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT_ST.description: The masked interrupt status of RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT.

TX_EOF_INT_ST.description: The masked interrupt status of TX_EOF_INT.

TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear TX_FIFO_REMPTY_INT.

RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear RX_FIFO_WOVF_INT.

TX_EOF_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear TX_EOF_INT.

RX_CNT.description: Indicates the cycle number of reading Rx FIFO.

RX_FIFO_WR_BIT_CNT.description: Indicates the current written bit number into Rx FIFO.

RX_FIFO_RD_BIT_CNT.description: Indicates the current read bit number from Rx FIFO.

TX_CNT.description: Indicates the cycle number of reading Tx FIFO.

TX_FIFO_RD_BIT_CNT.description: Indicates the current read bit number from Tx FIFO.

RX_CLK_I_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the input Rx core clock.

RX_CLK_O_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the output Rx core clock.

TX_CLK_I_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the input Tx core clock.

TX_CLK_O_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the output Tx core clock.

INT_RAW.description: Read only register for error and done

INT_CLR.description: Read only register for error and done

INT_ST.description: Read only register for error and done

TO_MEM_MAC.description: mac sw backup direction(reg to mem / mem to reg)

FILTER_THRES_U.description:
This sets the maximum threshold, in APB_CLK cycles, for the filter.

Any pulses with width less than this will be ignored when the filter is enabled.

FILTER_EN_U.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's input filter.

THR_ZERO_EN_U.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's zero comparator.

THR_H_LIM_EN_U.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's thr_h_lim comparator. Configures it to enable the high limit interrupt.

THR_L_LIM_EN_U.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's thr_l_lim comparator. Configures it to enable the low limit interrupt.

THR_THRES1_EN_U.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's thres1 comparator.

CH0_NEG_MODE_U.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a negative edge.

1: Increase the counter.2: Decrease the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

CH0_POS_MODE_U.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a positive edge.

1: Increase the counter.2: Decrease the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

CH0_HCTRL_MODE_U.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CH0_LCTRL_MODE_U.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CH1_NEG_MODE_U.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a negative edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

CH1_POS_MODE_U.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a positive edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

CH1_HCTRL_MODE_U.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CH1_LCTRL_MODE_U.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CNT_THRES1_U.description: This register is used to configure the thres1 value for unit %s.

CNT_H_LIM_U.description: This register is used to configure the thr_h_lim value for unit %s. When pcnt reaches this value, the counter will be cleared to 0.

CNT_L_LIM_U.description: This register is used to configure the thr_l_lim value for unit %s. When pcnt reaches this value, the counter will be cleared to 0.

CNT_THR_ZERO_MODE_U.description: The pulse counter status of PCNT_U%s corresponding to 0. 0: pulse counter decreases from positive to 0. 1: pulse counter increases from negative to 0. 2: pulse counter is negative. 3: pulse counter is positive.

BLEND1_CLUT_MEM_RDADDR_RST.description: Write 1 then write 0 to reset the read address of BLEND1 CLUT in fifo mode.

BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_FORCE_PD.description: 1: force power down BLEND CLUT memory.

BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_FORCE_PU.description: 1: force power up BLEND CLUT memory.

BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_CLK_ENA.description: 1: Force clock on for BLEND CLUT memory.

SR_EOF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when scaling and rotating engine calculate one frame image.

BLEND_EOF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when blending engine calculate one frame image.

SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the configured scaling and rotating coefficient is wrong. User can check the reasons through register PPA_SR_PARAM_ERR_ST_REG.

SR_EOF_INT_ST.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the PPA_SR_EOF_INT interrupt.

BLEND_EOF_INT_ST.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the PPA_BLEND_EOF_INT interrupt.

SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_ST.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the PPA_SR_RX_YSCAL_ERR_INT interrupt.

SR_EOF_INT_ENA.description: The interrupt enable bit for the PPA_SR_EOF_INT interrupt.

BLEND_EOF_INT_ENA.description: The interrupt enable bit for the PPA_BLEND_EOF_INT interrupt.

SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_ENA.description: The interrupt enable bit for the PPA_SR_RX_YSCAL_ERR_INT interrupt.

SR_EOF_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the PPA_SR_EOF_INT interrupt.

BLEND_EOF_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the PPA_BLEND_EOF_INT interrupt.

SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the PPA_SR_RX_YSCAL_ERR_INT interrupt.

SR_RX_CM.description: The source image color mode for Scaling and Rotating engine Rx. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 8: YUV420. others: Reserved.

SR_TX_CM.description: The destination image color mode for Scaling and Rotating engine Tx. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 8: YUV420. others: Reserved.

YUV_RX_RANGE.description: YUV input range when reg_sr_rx_cm is 4'd8. 0: limit range. 1: full range

YUV_TX_RANGE.description: YUV output range when reg_sr_tx_cm is 4'd8. 0: limit range. 1: full range

YUV2RGB_PROTOCAL.description: YUV to RGB protocal when reg_sr_rx_cm is 4'd8. 0: BT601. 1: BT709

RGB2YUV_PROTOCAL.description: RGB to YUV protocal when reg_sr_tx_cm is 4'd8. 0: BT601. 1: BT709

BLEND0_RX_CM.description: The source image color mode for background plane. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 3: Reserved. 4: L8. 5: L4.

BLEND1_RX_CM.description: The source image color mode for foreground plane. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 3: Reserved. 4: L8. 5: L4. 6: A8. 7: A4.

BLEND_TX_CM.description: The destination image color mode for output of blender. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 3: Reserved..

SR_RX_BYTE_SWAP_EN.description: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in byte. The Byte0 and Byte1 would be swapped while byte 2 and byte 3 would be swappped.

SR_RX_RGB_SWAP_EN.description: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in rgb. It means rgb would be swap to bgr.

SR_MACRO_BK_RO_BYPASS.description: Set this bit to 1 to bypass the macro block order function. This function is used to improve efficient accessing external memory.

BLEND0_RX_BYTE_SWAP_EN.description: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in byte. The Byte0 and Byte1 would be swapped while byte 2 and byte 3 would be swappped.

BLEND1_RX_BYTE_SWAP_EN.description: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in byte. The Byte0 and Byte1 would be swapped while byte 2 and byte 3 would be swappped.

BLEND0_RX_RGB_SWAP_EN.description: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in rgb. It means rgb would be swap to bgr.

BLEND1_RX_RGB_SWAP_EN.description: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in rgb. It means rgb would be swap to bgr.

BLEND_EN.description: Set this bit to enable alpha blending.

BLEND_BYPASS.description: Set this bit to bypass blender. Then background date would be output.

BLEND_FIX_PIXEL_FILL_EN.description: This bit is used to enable fix pixel filling. When this mode is enable  only Tx channel is work and the output pixel is configured by PPA_OUT_FIX_PIXEL.

UPDATE.description: Set this bit to update the transfer mode. Only the bit is set  the transfer mode is valid.

BLEND_RST.description: write 1 then write 0 to reset blending engine.

SR_RX_FIX_ALPHA.description: The value would replace the alpha value in received pixel for Scaling and Rotating engine when PPA_SR_RX_ALPHA_CONF_EN is enabled.

SR_RX_ALPHA_MOD.description: Alpha mode. 0/3: not replace alpha. 1: replace alpha with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA. 2: Original alpha multiply with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA/256.

SR_RX_ALPHA_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the original alpha value. When RX color mode is RGB565/RGB88. The original alpha value is 255.

BLEND_HB.description: The horizontal width of image block that would be filled in fix pixel filling mode. The unit is pixel

BLEND_VB.description: The vertical width of image block that would be filled in fix pixel filling mode. The unit is pixel

BLEND0_RX_FIX_ALPHA.description: The value would replace the alpha value in received pixel for background plane of blender when PPA_BLEND0_RX_ALPHA_CONF_EN is enabled.

BLEND1_RX_FIX_ALPHA.description: The value would replace the alpha value in received pixel for foreground plane of blender when PPA_BLEND1_RX_ALPHA_CONF_EN is enabled.

BLEND0_RX_ALPHA_MOD.description: Alpha mode. 0/3: not replace alpha. 1: replace alpha with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA. 2: Original alpha multiply with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA/256.

BLEND1_RX_ALPHA_MOD.description: Alpha mode. 0/3: not replace alpha. 1: replace alpha with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA. 2: Original alpha multiply with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA/256.

BLEND0_RX_ALPHA_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the original alpha value. When RX color mode is RGB565/RGB88. The original alpha value is 255.

BLEND1_RX_ALPHA_INV.description: Set this bit to invert the original alpha value. When RX color mode is RGB565/RGB88. The original alpha value is 255.

BLEND_TX_FIX_PIXEL.description: The configure fix pixel in fix pixel filling mode for blender engine.

COLORKEY_FG_B_LOW.description: color key lower threshold of foreground b channel

COLORKEY_FG_G_LOW.description: color key lower threshold of foreground g channel

COLORKEY_FG_R_LOW.description: color key lower threshold of foreground r channel

COLORKEY_FG_B_HIGH.description: color key higher threshold of foreground b channel

COLORKEY_FG_G_HIGH.description: color key higher threshold of foreground g channel

COLORKEY_FG_R_HIGH.description: color key higher threshold of foreground r channel

COLORKEY_BG_B_LOW.description: color key lower threshold of background b channel

COLORKEY_BG_G_LOW.description: color key lower threshold of background g channel

COLORKEY_BG_R_LOW.description: color key lower threshold of background r channel

COLORKEY_BG_B_HIGH.description: color key higher threshold of background b channel

COLORKEY_BG_G_HIGH.description: color key higher threshold of background g channel

COLORKEY_BG_R_HIGH.description: color key higher threshold of background r channel

COLORKEY_DEFAULT_B.description: default B channle value of color key

COLORKEY_DEFAULT_G.description: default G channle value of color key

COLORKEY_DEFAULT_R.description: default R channle value of color key

COLORKEY_FG_BG_REVERSE.description: when pixel in bg ck range but not in fg ck range, 0: the result is bg, 1: the result is fg

SR_SCAL_X_INT.description: The integrated part of scaling coefficient in X direction.

SR_SCAL_X_FRAG.description: The fragment part of scaling coefficient in X direction.

SR_SCAL_Y_INT.description: The integrated part of scaling coefficient in Y direction.

SR_SCAL_Y_FRAG.description: The fragment part of scaling coefficient in Y direction.

SR_ROTATE_ANGLE.description: The rotate angle. 0: 0 degree. 1: 90 degree. 2: 180 degree. 3: 270 degree.

SCAL_ROTATE_RST.description: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset scaling and rotating engine.

SCAL_ROTATE_START.description: Write 1 to enable scaling and rotating engine after parameter is configured.

SR_MIRROR_X.description: Image mirror in X direction. 0: disable, 1: enable

SR_MIRROR_Y.description: Image mirror in Y direction. 0: disable, 1: enable

SR_MEM_CLK_ENA.description: Set this bit to force clock enable of scaling and rotating engine's data memory.

SR_MEM_FORCE_PD.description: Set this bit to force power down scaling and rotating engine's data memory.

SR_MEM_FORCE_PU.description: Set this bit to force power up scaling and rotating engine's data memory.

CLK_EN.description: PPA register clock gate enable signal.

BLEND0_CLUT_CNT.description: The write data counter of BLEND0 CLUT in fifo mode.

BLEND1_CLUT_CNT.description: The write data counter of BLEND1 CLUT in fifo mode.

BLEND_SIZE_DIFF_ST.description: 1: indicate the size of two image is different.

TX_DSCR_VB_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the scaled VB plus the offset of Y coordinate in 2DDMA receive descriptor is larger than VA in 2DDMA receive descriptor.

TX_DSCR_HB_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the scaled HB plus the offset of X coordinate in 2DDMA receive descriptor is larger than HA in 2DDMA receive descriptor.

Y_RX_SCAL_EQUAL_0_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the PPA_SR_SCAL_Y_INT and PPA_SR_CAL_Y_FRAG both are 0.

RX_DSCR_VB_ERR_ST.description: The error is that VB in 2DDMA receive descriptor plus the offset of Y coordinate in 2DDMA transmit descriptor is larger than VA in 2DDMA transmit descriptor

YDST_LEN_TOO_SAMLL_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the scaled image width is 0. For example.  when source width is 14. scaled value is 1/16. and no rotate operation. then scaled width would be 0 as the result would be floored.

YDST_LEN_TOO_LARGE_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the scaled width is larger than (2^13 - 1).

X_RX_SCAL_EQUAL_0_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the scaled image height is 0.

RX_DSCR_HB_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the HB in 2DDMA transmit descriptor plus the offset of X coordinate in 2DDMA transmit descriptor is larger than HA in 2DDMA transmit descriptor.

XDST_LEN_TOO_SAMLL_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the scaled image height is 0. For example.  when source height is 14. scaled value is 1/16. and no rotate operation. then scaled height would be 0 as the result would be floored.

XDST_LEN_TOO_LARGE_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the scaled image height is larger than (2^13 - 1).

X_YUV420_RX_SCALE_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the ha/hb/x param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 rx

Y_YUV420_RX_SCALE_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the va/vb/y param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 rx

X_YUV420_TX_SCALE_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the ha/hb/x param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 tx

Y_YUV420_TX_SCALE_ERR_ST.description: The error is that the va/vb/y param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 tx

PMUP_CHANNEL_CFG.description: configure the code of valid pump channel code

CLK_EN.description: force register clken

TX_CH%sDATA.description: The read and write  data register for CHANNEL%s by apb fifo access.

RX_CH%sDATA.description: The read and write  data register for CHANNEL$n by apb fifo access.

CHDATA.description: Read and write data for channel %s via APB FIFO.
Read and write data for channel 0 via APB FIFO.

TX_START_CH0.description: Set this bit to start sending data on CHANNEL%s.

MEM_RD_RST_CH0.description: Set this bit to reset read ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing transmitter.

APB_MEM_RST_CH0.description: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

TX_CONTI_MODE_CH0.description: Set this bit to restart transmission  from the first data to the last data in CHANNEL%s.

MEM_TX_WRAP_EN_CH0.description: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume sending at the start when the data to be sent is more than its memory size.

IDLE_OUT_LV_CH0.description: This bit configures the level of output signal in CHANNEL%s when the latter is in IDLE state.

IDLE_OUT_EN_CH0.description: This is the output enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s in IDLE state.

TX_STOP_CH0.description: Set this bit to stop the transmitter of CHANNEL%s sending data out.

DIV_CNT_CH0.description: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

MEM_SIZE_CH0.description: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

CARRIER_EFF_EN_CH0.description: 1: Add carrier modulation on the output signal only at the send data state for CHANNEL%s. 0: Add carrier modulation on the output signal at all state for CHANNEL%s. Only valid when RMT_CARRIER_EN_CH%s is 1.

CARRIER_EN_CH0.description: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

CARRIER_OUT_LV_CH0.description: This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

DIV_CNT_CH4.description: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

IDLE_THRES_CH4.description: When no edge is detected on the input signal and continuous clock cycles is longer than this register value, received process is finished.

MEM_SIZE_CH4.description: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

CARRIER_EN_CH4.description: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

CARRIER_OUT_LV_CH4.description: This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

RX_EN_CH4.description: Set this bit to enable receiver to receive data on CHANNEL%s.

MEM_WR_RST_CH4.description: Set this bit to reset write ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing receiver.

APB_MEM_RST_CH4.description: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

MEM_OWNER_CH4.description: This register marks the ownership of CHANNEL%s's ram block.1'h1: Receiver is using the ram. 1'h0: APB bus is using the ram.

RX_FILTER_EN_CH4.description: This is the receive filter's enable bit for CHANNEL%s.

RX_FILTER_THRES_CH4.description: Ignores the input pulse when its width is smaller than this register value in APB clock periods (in receive mode).

MEM_RX_WRAP_EN_CH4.description: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume receiving at the start when the data to be received is more than its memory size.

MEM_RADDR_EX_CH0.description: This register records the memory address offset when transmitter of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

APB_MEM_WADDR_CH0.description: This register records the memory address offset when writes RAM over APB bus.

STATE_CH0.description: This register records the FSM status of CHANNEL%s.

MEM_EMPTY_CH0.description: This status bit will be set when the data to be set is more than memory size and the wraparound mode is disabled.

APB_MEM_WR_ERR_CH0.description: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when writes via APB bus.

MEM_WADDR_EX_CH4.description: This register records the memory address offset when receiver of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

APB_MEM_RADDR_CH4.description: This register records the memory address offset when reads RAM over APB bus.

STATE_CH4.description: This register records the FSM status of CHANNEL%s.

MEM_OWNER_ERR_CH4.description: This status bit will be set when the ownership of memory block is wrong.

MEM_FULL_CH4.description: This status bit will be set if the receiver receives more data than the memory size.

APB_MEM_RD_ERR_CH4.description: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when reads via APB bus.
