APP_CTRL0_INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable the interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT.

APP_CTRL1_INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable the interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT.

RX_START_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_RX_START_INT.

TX_START_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_TX_START_INT.

RX_HUNG_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT.

TX_HUNG_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT.

SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_SEND_S_REG_Q_INT.

SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_SEND_A_REG_Q_INT.

OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_OUT_EOF_INT.

APP_CTRL0_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT.

APP_CTRL1_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the raw interrupt of UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT.

CHECK_SUM_EN.description: Set this bit to enable head checksum check when receiving.

CHECK_SEQ_EN.description: Set this bit to  enable sequence number check when receiving.

CRC_DISABLE.description: Set this bit to support CRC calculation, and data integrity check bit should 1.

SAVE_HEAD.description: Set this bit to save data packet head when UHCI receive data.

TX_CHECK_SUM_RE.description: Set this bit to encode data packet with checksum.

TX_ACK_NUM_RE.description: Set this bit to encode data packet with ACK when reliable data packet is ready.

WAIT_SW_START.description: Set this bit to enable UHCI encoder transfer to ST_SW_WAIT status.

SW_START.description: Set this bit to transmit data packet if UCHI_ENCODE_STATE is ST_SW_WAIT.

RX_ERR_CAUSE.description: Indicates the error types when DMA receives the error frame. 3'b001: UHCI packet checksum error. 3'b010: UHCI packet sequence number error. 3'b011: UHCI packet CRC bit error. 3'b100: find 0xC0, but received packet is uncompleted. 3'b101: 0xC0 is not found, but received packet is completed. 3'b110: CRC check error.

TX_C0_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable resolve char 0xC0 when DMA receiving data.

TX_DB_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable resolve char 0xDB when DMA receiving data.

TX_11_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable resolve flow control char 0x11 when DMA receiving data.

TX_13_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable resolve flow control char 0x13 when DMA receiving data.

RX_C0_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable replacing 0xC0 with special char when DMA receiving data.

RX_DB_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable replacing 0xDB with special char when DMA receiving data.

RX_11_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable replacing 0x11 with special char when DMA receiving data.

RX_13_ESC_EN.description: Set this bit to enable replacing 0x13 with special char when DMA receiving data.

TXFIFO_TIMEOUT.description: Stores the timeout value. DMA generates UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT for timeout when receiving data.

TXFIFO_TIMEOUT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable TX FIFO timeout when receiving.

RXFIFO_TIMEOUT.description: Stores the timeout value. DMA generates UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT for timeout when reading RAM data.

RXFIFO_TIMEOUT_ENA.description: Set this bit to enable TX FIFO timeout when DMA sending data.

ACK_NUM.description: Indicates the ACK number during software flow control.

LOAD.description: Set this bit to load the ACK value of UHCI_ACK_NUM.

RX_HEAD.description: Stores the head of received packet.

SINGLE_SEND_EN.description: Set this bit to enable sending short packet with single_send mode.

ALWAYS_SEND_EN.description: Set this bit to enable sending short packet with always_send mode.

SEND_Q0_WORD0.description: Serves as quick sending register in specified mode in UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

SEND_Q0_WORD1.description: Serves as quick sending register in specified mode in UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

SEND_Q5_WORD0.description: Serves as quick sending register in specified mode in UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

SEND_Q6_WORD1.description: Serves as quick sending register in specified mode in UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

SEPER_CHAR.description: Configures the delimiter for encoding, default value is 0xC0.

SEPER_ESC_CHAR0.description: Configures the first char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDB.

SEPER_ESC_CHAR1.description: Configures the second char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDC.

ESC_SEQ0.description: Configures the char needing encoding, which is 0xDB as flow control char by default.

ESC_SEQ0_CHAR0.description: Configures the first char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDB.

ESC_SEQ0_CHAR1.description: Configures the second char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDD.

ESC_SEQ1.description: Configures the char needing encoding, which is 0x11 as flow control char by default.

ESC_SEQ1_CHAR0.description: Configures the first char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDB.

ESC_SEQ1_CHAR1.description: Configures the second char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDE.

ESC_SEQ2.description: Configures the char needing encoding, which is 0x13 as flow control char by default.

ESC_SEQ2_CHAR0.description: Configures the first char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDB.

ESC_SEQ2_CHAR1.description: Configures the second char of SLIP escape character, default value is 0xDF.

PKT_THRS.description: Configures the data packet's maximum length when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 0.

EP1.description: FIFO access for the CDC-ACM data IN and OUT endpoints.

EP1_CONF.description: Configuration and control registers for the CDC-ACM FIFOs.

TEST.description: Registers used for debugging the PHY.

JFIFO_ST.description: JTAG FIFO status and control registers.

FRAM_NUM.description: Last received SOF frame index register.

IN_EP2_ST.description: CDC-ACM interrupt IN endpoint status information.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_RDWR_BYTE.description: Write and read byte data to/from UART Tx/Rx FIFO through this field. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_IN_EMPTY_INT is set, then user can write data (up to 64 bytes) into UART Tx FIFO. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT is set, user can check USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP1_WR_ADDR USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP0_RD_ADDR to know how many data is received, then read data from UART Rx FIFO.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_WR_DONE.description: Set this bit to indicate writing byte data to UART Tx FIFO is done.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_IN_EP_DATA_FREE.description: 1'b1: Indicate UART Tx FIFO is not full and can write data into in. After writing USB_DEVICE_WR_DONE, this bit would be 0 until data in UART Tx FIFO is read by USB Host.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_OUT_EP_DATA_AVAIL.description: 1'b1: Indicate there is data in UART Rx FIFO.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_JTAG_IN_FLUSH_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when flush cmd is received for IN endpoint 2 of JTAG.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SOF_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when SOF frame is received.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT_.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Serial Port OUT Endpoint received one packet.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_IN_EMPTY_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Serial Port IN Endpoint is empty.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_PID_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when pid error is detected.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_CRC5_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when CRC5 error is detected.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_CRC16_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when CRC16 error is detected.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_STUFF_ERR_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when stuff error is detected.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_IN_TOKEN_REC_IN_EP1_INT_.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when IN token for IN endpoint 1 is received.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_USB_BUS_RESET_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when usb bus reset is detected.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP1_ZERO_PAYLOAD_INT.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when OUT endpoint 1 received packet with zero palyload.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP2_ZERO_PAYLOAD_INT.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when OUT endpoint 2 received packet with zero palyload.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_DTR_CHG_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level of DTR from usb serial channel is changed.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SET_LINE_CODE_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level of SET LINE CODING request is received.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP0_WR_ADDR.description: Write data address of OUT endpoint 0. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT is detected, there are USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP0_WR_ADDR-2 bytes data in OUT EP0.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP0_RD_ADDR.description: Read data address of OUT endpoint 0.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP1_WR_ADDR.description: Write data address of OUT endpoint 1. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT is detected, there are USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP1_WR_ADDR-2 bytes data in OUT EP1.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP1_RD_ADDR.description: Read data address of OUT endpoint 1.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP1_REC_DATA_CNT.description: Data count in OUT endpoint 1 when one packet is received.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP2_WR_ADDR.description: Write data address of OUT endpoint 2. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT is detected, there are USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP2_WR_ADDR-2 bytes data in OUT EP2.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_OUT_EP2_RD_ADDR.description: Read data address of OUT endpoint 2.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_CLK_EN.description: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_USB_MEM_CLK_EN.description: 1: Force clock on for usb memory.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_RTS.description: 1: Chip reset is detected from usb serial channel. Software write 1 to clear it.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_DTR.description: 1: Chip reset is detected from usb jtag channel. Software write 1 to clear it.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_USB_UART_CHIP_RST_DIS.description: Set this bit to disable chip reset from usb serial channel to reset chip.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_DW_DTE_RATE.description: The value of dwDTERate set by host through SET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_BCHAR_FORMAT.description: The value of bCharFormat set by host through SET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_BPARITY_TYPE.description: The value of bParityTpye set by host through SET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_BDATA_BITS.description: The value of bDataBits set by host through SET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_GET_DW_DTE_RATE.description: The value of dwDTERate set by software which is requested by GET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_GET_BDATA_BITS.description: The value of bCharFormat set by software which is requested by GET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_GET_BPARITY_TYPE.description: The value of bParityTpye set by software which is requested by GET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_GET_BCHAR_FORMAT.description: The value of bDataBits set by software which is requested by GET_LINE_CODING command.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_CONFIG_UPDATE.description: Write 1 to this register would update the value of configure registers from APB clock domain to 48MHz clock domain.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_IN_AFIFO_RESET_WR.description: Write 1 to reset CDC_ACM IN async FIFO write clock domain.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_IN_AFIFO_RESET_RD.description: Write 1 to reset CDC_ACM IN async FIFO read clock domain.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_OUT_AFIFO_RESET_W.description: Write 1 to reset CDC_ACM OUT async FIFO write clock domain.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_OUT_AFIFO_RESET_R.description: Write 1 to reset CDC_ACM OUT async FIFO read clock domain.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_OUT_AFIFO_REMPTY.description: CDC_ACM OUTOUT async FIFO empty signal in read clock domain.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_SERIAL_IN_AFIFO_WFULL.description: CDC_ACM OUT IN async FIFO empty signal in write clock domain.

USB_SERIAL_JTAG_USB_BUS_RESET_ST.description: USB bus reset status. 0: USB-Serial-JTAG is in usb bus reset status. 1: USB bus reset is released.
